title: baked beans
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: none such cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat shortening and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients; gradually add to shortening mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in mincemeat.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Frost if desired. Makes about 6 1/2 dozen.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, carrots and green pepper.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand 1 hour.
Drain if water accumulates.
Combine sugar, mustard, water, vinegar and celery seed.
Bring to a boil; boil 3 minutes.
Cool.
Pour over cabbage; let stand 3 minutes.
Stir well.
Freeze in containers.
To serve, thaw in refrigerator.

title: white icing
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick (will be solid) and cool completely.
Cream butter with sugar and cooled white sauce, beat until foamy.
Add vanilla.
This will not get sugary or crusty. Freezes well.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar; mix and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake crust for 10 minutes at 375°; cool. Cream 1 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip; spread over pretzel layer.
Mix Jell-O and boiling water; add frozen strawberries (practically thawed).
Pour over second layer. Refrigerate.
Best to make night before.

title: no bake fudge cookie
directions: Boil milk, butter, sugar, cocoa and salt until a little ball hardens in cold water.
Stir frequently.
Lay tinfoil 20-inches in length out.
After fudge hardens, add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix, spoon out fudge onto foil.
Cool.
Happy eats to you.

title: lo-cal vegetable omelet
directions: Cut; measure carrots and onion.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in 10-inch skillet over medium heat, about 3 minutes.
Slice mushrooms.
Add carrots, onion, mushrooms and 1/8 teaspoon salt to skillet.
Saute 10 minutes or until tender.
Measure remaining ingredients.
Combine eggs, milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper in bowl.
Beat with rotary beater until blended.
Remove vegetables to another bowl from skillet.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in same skillet over low heat, about 1 minute.
Pour eggs into skillet. As egg mixture sets, lift with spatula to allow uncooked portions to flow to bottom of skillet.
Cook 10 minutes or until egg is completely set.
Loosen edges of omelet.
Spoon cooked vegetables over omelet.
Fold in half and remove to serving platter.
Makes 4 servings.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Line baking sheet with foil.
Combine butter, corn syrup, water and salt in a heavy 1 quart saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Stir in pecans, mixing to coat well.
Spread evenly on baking sheet and bake 1 hour, stirring about every 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Stir to cool.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix flour, sugar and yeast, then add remaining ingredients. Put into greased muffin tins about 3/4 full.
Mixture may be stored in refrigerator.
Cook at 400° until done.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables and marinate overnight in following dressing mixture:

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans as directed.
Save water of beans and mix with other ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Put in casserole dish topped with the bread crumbs that have been browned in skillet. Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Mix other ingredients. Refrigerate.
Can be made up to a week prior to using.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then lower oven to 350° and bake for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: cucumbers in cream sauce
directions: With sliced cucumbers, add slivers of onion.

title: spicy prune muffins
directions: Cook prunes according to package directions.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Add enough milk to prune liquid to equal 1 cup; set aside.
Chop prunes; set aside.
Beat butter at medium speed with mixer until creamy; gradually add brown sugar.
Beat well. Add egg, beating until blended.
Combine flour and next four ingredients; add to butter mixture, alternately with milk mixture beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat at low speed until blended after each addition.
Stir in chopped prunes and vanilla. Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 22 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately. Makes approximately 15 muffins.

title: summer sole with spring vegies
directions: Sprinkle one side of each fillet with pepper, paprika and Parmesan.
Roll each fillet with seasoned salt on the inside. Arrange in a 9-inch, round baking dish, seam side down.
Set aside.

title: coconut date balls
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients 3 minutes. Then mix the Rice Krispies and pecans. Pour date mixture over and mix. Make balls with the mixture and roll in coconut.

title: impossible turkey pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle turkey, mushrooms, onions, salt and cheese in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high. Pour onto plate and bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Mix meat, seasonings, soup and beans in a 9 x 9-inch pan or casserole dish.
Spread potatoes over this mixture.
Top with butter and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet "n" sour meat loaf
directions: Mix tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard together. Mix egg, onion, crackers, meat, salt and pepper.
Shape meat into oval loaf. Place in shallow baking dish.
Pour rest of tomato sauce mixture on top.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: murray's favorite lemony-mustard dressing
directions: Grate 2 teaspoons peel from lemon; squeeze juice from lemon to make 1/4 cup.
In a small bowl, with wire whisk or fork, mix lemon peel, lemon juice, olive oil and remaining ingredients.
Pour dressing over salad greens (spinach, Boston lettuce, Belgian endives) and sliced mushrooms.
Gently toss to mix well.

title: mary's fresh strawberry (or peach) pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch in saucepan. Stir in water gradually. Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add gelatin powder. Stir until dissolved.
Stir in lemon juice. Cool glaze.
Arrange strawberries in baked pie shell. Pour glaze over berries and refrigerate until set, about 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Remove top and seeds from peppers and parboil 5 minutes; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients except bacon slices.
Stuff peppers and stand upright in greased baking dish.
Place bacon strips on top of peppers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: persimmon or date cake
directions: Chop dates or persimmons.
Add to raisins and nuts.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix thoroughly with fruit.
Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Pour over flour and fruit-nut mix.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in fruit.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Separate rolls and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°, or until brown.
Cool. Combine cream cheese, sour cream and dressing mix.
Beat until smooth.
Spread on crust.
Chop all vegetables fine.
Sprinkle on cream cheese.
Chill.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix and put in unbaked pie shell; top with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 1 pie.

title: chutney cheese spread
directions: Combine cheese, sherry, curry and salt.
Blend well.
Stir in chutney; chill.
Turn into dish.
Top with chives.

title: make ahead stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Combine beef, rice, onion, chili powder and salt.
Mix well. Divide into 8 equal portions.
Cut the stiff ridge from the back of each cabbage leaf.
Cook leaves in boiling water, 2 at a time, just until they are limp; drain well.
Place one portion of the meat mixture at stem end of each cabbage leaf and roll up, folding the sides of the leaves over meat mixture.
Arrange rolls in plastic container with fitted lid.
Seal and freeze.
When ready to use, arrange frozen cabbage rolls in large frying pan.

title: chicken crunch sandwich
directions: Mix together chicken, soup, gravy, water chestnuts, pimento and onion.
Heap as much as you can on slice of bread.
Cover with top slice of bread.
Wrap each sandwich in foil and freeze.
When ready to serve (do not defrost) dip each sandwich in mixture made from combining beaten eggs and milk, then in crushed potato chips. Bake on well-buttered cookie sheet at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 11 people.
Can be prepared ahead.
Total cooking time: 1 hour, uncovered.

title: peanut dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.

title: holiday green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, soup, milk, pepper and 1/2 can of onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with the remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Put sliced cucumbers in stone jar.
Add salt to 1 gallon boiling water.
Pour over cucumbers. Let stand for 1 week. Drain and wash cucumbers.
Add alum to 1 gallon boiling water. Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand for 24 hours.
Drain and wash.

title: split pea soup
directions: Boil hard for 20 minutes.
Then simmer until peas are done which should be 2 hours.
Serve with hot corn bread and butter. Serves 6.

title: mexican onion-beef skillet
directions: Saute onion
with
ground
beef for 10 minutes or until onions are
tender.
Stir
in
enchilada sauce and water.
Add salt to taste.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in corn chips.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese. Makes 4 servings.

title: savory red cabbage
directions: Saute onions in fat until soft and golden (approximately 10 minutes).
Add all other ingredients.
Cover and cook gently until cabbage is tender, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add raisins, butter and beaten eggs; mix well.
Add buttermilk; blend together.
Pour into a well-greased iron skillet or baking tin.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: chocolate fudge cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add condensed milk.
Blend in flour, vanilla and pecans.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 6 to 9 minutes.
Remove while cookies look underbaked.
Do not overbake. Makes 6 dozen.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and cook noodles.
Mix sausage, noodles and soup in large bowl or casserole dish.
Grate cheese on top.
Cook until cheese is melted.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas and mix well.
Mix flour, salt and soda.
Add flour and sour milk alternately to first mixture.
Stir in nuts and beat well.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried rice
directions: Drain bean sprouts; soak in cold water.
Put small amount of oil in 4-quart pan.
Cook cabbage, onions and celery until slightly brown.
Add hamburger and other ingredients.
Drain water from bean sprouts; add sprouts to pan.
Cook on low heat for 15 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
May add soy sauce, if you like.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks to lemon yellow color.
Add sugar.
Gradually add flour and water alternately.
Add baking powder and salt. Beat after each addition.
Beat egg whites until they form a peak. Fold into batter.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Cream together all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shells (not the deep-dish). Bake in 400° oven for 25 to 35 minutes. Makes 3 or 4 pies.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Mix 1 or 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add dry taco seasoning, onion and water.
Stir to mix.
Crush taco flavored Doritos and put in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread hamburger mixture over Doritos. Spread tomato over hamburger.
Spread shredded lettuce over tomato.
Mix cheese soup with milk and pour over lettuce.
Top with shredded Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: in-a-hurry taco bake
directions: Crush corn chips and place in bottom of a small casserole dish. Top with beans, corn, peppers, onions, salsa and cheese, in that order.
Microwave for 8 to 10 minutes, or bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: western style pork chops
directions: Dip both sides of pork chops in taco sauce, then in crushed tortilla chips.
Coat both sides well.
Place in a greased baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until tender.
Remove from dish with turner.
Serves 4.

title: indian punch
directions: Boil sugar, water and lemon juice for 3 minutes.
Cool. Combine with tea, vanilla and almond extracts.
Immediately before serving, add ginger ale and pour over chipped ice.
Yield:
1 gallon.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to boil and pour over pork roast.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all except cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Place in large rectangular dish.
Top with cheese, chips and almonds.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pepper steak
directions: Mix the oil, soy sauce and garlic; pour over steak in bowl. Let stand at least 1 hour.
Brown meat in oil sauce in heavy pan. Add onion and celery; cook for 5 to 10 minutes over low heat.
Mix cornstarch and water (1/4 cup).
Add to pan; stir well until thick.
Add tomatoes and cook until steak is tender.
Add sweet pepper; cook until pepper is barely done.
Serve over boiled rice.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in molasses, sugar, salt and margarine. Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into a large, warm bowl. Sprinkle or crumble in yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm milk mixture.
Add 1 cup of whole wheat flour and 1 cup of white flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add enough of each kind of remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes. Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in place free from draft until doubled in bulk, about 40 minutes. Punch down and shape into desired rolls, dividing dough in half or thirds.
Brush lightly with melted margarine.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place free from draft until doubled in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Bake in hot oven (400°) about 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer vegetables in bowl in order listed.
Mix together mayonnaise and sugar; spread over top of peas.
Spread a bag of shredded cheddar cheese over the mayonnaise layer.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Prior to serving, mix together.

title: peaches and cream cheese cake
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients 2 minutes in small bowl and pour into greased 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
Place 15 to 20 ounce can of peaches or pineapple on top of batter (drain fruit well and reserve juice).
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and juice.
Beat for 2 minutes and spoon on top of peaches 1-inch from edge.
Combine 1 tablespoon of sugar, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon and sprinkle over cream cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is golden brown.
Filling will appear soft.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Mix well in pint jar and store in refrigerator.
Keeps for several weeks.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, margarine and milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly, to prevent scorching.
Boil for 4 minutes and remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until melted. Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: country vanilla ice cream
directions: Add sugar gradually to beaten eggs.
Continue to beat until mixture is very stiff.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into gallon freezer and freeze as directed (no cooking).

title: chili beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain; add all other ingredients and cook for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, and oil with seasoning packet from ramen noodles. Break up ramen noodles into small pieces. Mix all ingredients together.

title: buttermilk rolls (kolachi)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Beat egg yolks, egg, oleo, salt and sugar.
Warm buttermilk and soda.
Mix all together except flour.
Add flour gradually and knead for 8 minutes until a smooth ball.
Let rise until double in size.
Make crescent rolls or fill with your favorite fruit filling.
Let rise again and bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes until brown.
Brush dough with melted butter each time you let it rise and after baking.

title: apricot brandy cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Spread chopped pecans in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix, pudding, water, oil and eggs well.
Pour batter in pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: oodles fiesta casserole
directions: Prepare 1 cup Jack cheese, 1/2 cup chillies, 1/4 cup black olives and 2 tablespoons pimiento.
Break up noodles and cook in 3 cups boiling water for 2 minutes.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Combine the seasoning from just 1 flavor packet, the Jack cheese, chillies, olives and pimiento with 1 cup sour cream. Spoon into a buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese and 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: disgustingly rich brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat inside of baking pan with butter. Melt your 2 cubes butter slowly on low burner.
Watch out!
It is easy to burn.
In your mixing bowl, stir cocoa and sugar together, then stir in melted butter.
Add the eggs and vanilla; stir again. Now add the flour.
Mix just until smooth.
Scrape the mixture into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread out with spatula.
Bake at 350°.
Bake just until the brownies begin to pull away from side of the pan, 40 minutes.

title: cherry-almond torte
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, except add almond extract with the water.
Pour into pan.
Bake and cool as directed.
Remove from pan.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook shells; drain.
Add chopped eggs, black olives, mayonnaise and mustard.
Season to taste.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook noodles by directions on package.
Cool.
Mix in other ingredients; chill and serve.
Very low fat.
Serves 2 or 3 people.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate 1 hour or more.
Roll, using as little flour as possible, and cut into favorite shapes.
May sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown Pork Chops - put in baking dish.
Prepare sauce and pour over chops.
Bake 1-1/2 hours at 325.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Combine nuts, 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon. Set aside.
Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Set aside. In a large bowl, cream the butter with electric mixer.
Gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar and continue to cream until light and fluffy. Add eggs, beating well after each. Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Gently beat flour mixture into creamed mixture until well blended.
Grease and flour a tube or Bundt pan.
Spoon 1/3 of the cake batter into pan and sprinkle with 1/3 of the nut mixture. Repeat twice more.
Rap bottom of pan against countertop.

Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cover top loosely with foil during the last 10 minutes of baking if the top gets too brown. Cool pan on rack 10 minutes, then turn cake onto rack to cool completely, nut side up.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook vegetables and spices
for 2 hours and put through strainer.
Add sugar, oil and cheese.
Cook 1 hour and seal.

title: potato sour cream casserole(serves 10 to 15)
directions: Mix altogether and spread in 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased Pyrex dish.
Cover tightly (aluminum foil).
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Uncover.
Sprinkle topping mixture.

title: banana split
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine (melted).
Mix well and press into dish.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard in a small bowl.
Set aside.
Combine egg, onion, cracker crumbs, ground beef, salt and pepper in a mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 of the tomato mixture and blend thoroughly.
Shape into an oval loaf pan and place in an oblong micro-proof baking dish.
Make a depression in top of loaf.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top of meat.
Cook, uncovered, on Medium for 25 to 30 minutes or until center is cooked.
Cover meat and let stand about 10 minutes before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in a greased baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 400°. The last 10 minutes of baking time, coat top of mixture with crushed corn flakes coated with melted oleo or butter.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine oatmeal, whole wheat flour, brown sugar, salt and margarine.
Pour boiling water over this and mix well.
When mixture is cooled to lukewarm combine yeast and warm water and add to cooled mixture.
Sti rin enough flour to make soft dough; knead until smooth.
Let rise in greased bowl, then shape into 2 loaves. Let rise, then bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate-peanut butter squares
directions: Mix all together and pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt 1 1/2 bags chocolate chips in microwave and pour onto peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate and cut into squares when firm.

title: make ahead potatoes
directions: Whip well and store in Tupperware up to 2 weeks.
Reheat in oven or microwave.

title: meatless vegetable soup(from an 1860 cookbook)
directions: Cook the onion in the butter until tender. Add the water, carrot, cabbage, celery, green beans, peas, salt and sugar.
Cook for 10 minutes. Add the tomatoes and potatoes.
Cook 2 more minutes. Sprinkle with the parsley on servings.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Brown meat in oil, along with the next 7 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger
with	onion
and bell pepper.
Drain. Put meat
in
bottom
of casserole dish. Brown rice in 1 or 2 tablespoons
of
butter.
Sprinkle	rice evenly over hamburger meat.
Salt rice as desired.
Put cabbage over rice (more salt if desired).
Pour
stewed
tomatoes with juice over cabbage; then one
can
water
over tomatoes.
Top with cheese.
Cover casserole and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: no mix meat loaf
directions: Shape meat into loaf 3 inches high on sheet of heavy duty foil.
Sprinkle soup over loaf; cover with cream soup.
Seal foil by folding over.
Bake in shallow pan 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Yields 8 servings.
Beef can be used if not thawed, simply bake for longer time.

title: endless coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage and peppers.
In a large bowl, combine the cabbage, peppers and onion; set aside.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix the pudding
with
milk, then mix a small amount of pudding into cream	cheese	until smooth.
Add all the pudding and the Cool Whip.
Crumble in the cookies.

title: baked onions
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion rings in butter until tender. Arrange onions in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Blend soup, milk, soy and pepper.
Pour over cheese and onions and mix lightly.
Arrange buttered bread slices over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, uncovered.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together first 5 dry ingredients.
In mixer bowl, beat well eggs, oil, sugars, etc.
Then mix in dry ingredients.
Set oven for 325°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Divide batter evenly between 2 loaves; bake for approximately 1 hour.
Remove from pans immediately.
This bread freezes well.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain clams; combine sour cream and remaining ingredients. Chill.
Serve with crackers, chips or veggies.

title: cranberry-orange upside-down cake
directions: Cover bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with melted butter; top with an even layer of brown sugar.
Cut orange slices in half; place in rows on top of sugar.
Sprinkle over cranberries; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar together until fluffy; beat in eggs until smooth.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to cream mixture alternately with milk and orange juice, beating until smooth.
Stir orange peel into batter.
Pour over cranberry-orange mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake is done. Immediately turn out onto platter or tray.
Garnish with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Place rice in greased baking dish. Place Chicken on top of rice. Sprinkle seasonings on top of chicken. Mix soup, water and milk and pour on top of chicken.
Bake in oven at 375 degrees for 30 minutes or until juices run clear.

title: spaghetti supreme salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate overnight. Serve cold. Improves with age. You may vary amounts of ingredients to suit your
taste.

title: cake icing(for decorating cakes)
directions: Beat the powdered milk and cold water until thick (like whipping cream).
Add the Crisco and salt; beat until creamy.
Add the powdered sugar and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy, about 4 minutes.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Mix together all ingredients, only use half of the Doritos in the mixture and sprinkle the rest on top of the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fluffy potato bake(a tangy version of mashed potatoes)
directions: Cook, peel and mash potatoes.
In saucepan, cook onion in 1/4 cup margarine until tender, but not brown.
Stir onion, cottage cheese, parsley and salt into mashed potatoes.
Spoon potato mixture into a well-greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Drizzle melted margarine over top, if desired.

title: sausage breakfast
directions: Brown breakfast sausage.
Add a layer of sliced potatoes and a layer of creamed corn.
Continue until casserole is full.
Put sausage on top.
Cover with tomato soup.
Bake in oven until done.

title: viva la chicken
directions: Cook and bone chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Cut corn tortillas into 1-inch strips or squares.
Combine soups, milk, onion and salsa.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange 1/2 of the tortillas in pan.
Top with half of the chicken, olives and mushrooms.
Repeat.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Top with full pound of cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: For crust:
Mix margarine that has been melted with flour. Press into an oblong pan.
Sprinkle pecans on top of batter and bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: buttermilk custard pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix corn, eggs, milk, oil, salt and pepper.
Stir in cornbread mix; put in 9 x 9-inch or 1 1/2-quart size baking pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°; let set a few minutes after removing from oven.

title: gillespie apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Add apples.
Mix well.
Pour in nuts.
Pour in greased 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours on 350°.
Sprinkle with nuts when done.

title: asian turkey or chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except meat and salsa, in shallow glass or plastic dish.
Add meat; turn to coat with marinade.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours, but no longer than 4 hours, turning once.

title: busy day taco casserole
directions: Brown meat in saucepan.
Combine soups, taco sauce and milk. Crush chips in bag.
Layer meat, Doritos and sauce until all gone. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: ranch style beans
directions: Cook ground beef in butter until the redness is gone.
Mix all ingredients together.
Salt to taste and bake at 400° about 30 minutes.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix all meat ball ingredients.
Put in one layer flat pan.

title: chocolate nut cookies
directions: Add flour, baking powder and salt to first 5 ingredients. Add nuts. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate crunch brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Stir in cocoa, flour and vanilla.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.
Cool.
Spread Marshmallow Creme over the brownies.
In small pan, melt peanut butter and chocolate chips over low heat.
(Can be done in a microwave.) Remove from heat and stir in cereal.
Spread over marshmallow layer.
Chill before cutting.
Store in refrigerator.

title: risotta milanese
directions: Remove sausage from casing and crumble.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Add sausage, onion, mushrooms and garlic.
Saute until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in rice and saute until rice is lightly browned.
Add chicken broth, wine or sherry.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: surprise cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and milk; set aside.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Line cupcake tins with paper cups. Fill cups with rounded teaspoonful of cake mix, then cream mixture, then cake mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 18 cupcakes.
Frost with your favorite icing.

title: chicken-cornbread casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Heat broth and soups and pour over crumbs; mix.
Add onions and celery; season to taste. If needed, add boiling water to moisten.
Grease casserole dish. Alternate layers of the chicken and the dressing mixture, beginning and ending with the dressing.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: braised beef fillet(favorite dish of the russian prince pripetskoi in his paris
directions: Put tomatoes briefly into hot water.
Remove skin and cut in halves.
Chop onions.
Wash, dry and chop herbs.
Rub meat with salt and pepper.

title: tomato rice soup
directions: Cut salt pork into cubes and saute with chopped onion.
Add crushed tomatoes and 4 cans of water.
Add beef bouillon cubes. Bring to a gentle boil.
Reduce heat and cook for about 10 minutes.
Return to gentle boil and add rice.
Simmer for just a little while.

title: blue cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter an 8-inch spring-form pan; sprinkle cracker crumbs on bottom and sides.
Blend cheeses, eggs, flour, salt, picante sauce and sour cream.
Fold in onions.
Pour mixture into pan and sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake for 1 hour.
Cool and chill overnight.
Garnish with parsley and tomato roses or with additional chopped green onions, if desired.
Serve at room temperature on crackers.
Makes 20 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 cup chopped pecans, crushed pineapple, bell pepper, onion, seasoned salt and Tabasco sauce and make into a ball.
Roll in cup chopped pecans and serve with crackers.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Brown chicken in 2 tablespoons oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove chicken.
Set aside.
Add onions to skillet.
Cook until tender.
Stir in paprika.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Add milk and egg and pour over cooked macaroni in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown hamburger and place on top of macaroni.
Mix pizza sauce and tomato soup.
Pour over top of hamburger.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt; mix well.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Toss apples with water and lemon juice.
Spoon into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle flour mixture over apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with cheese; bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: fast and easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat both soups and tomatoes together.
Warm the tortillas. Put chicken in each tortilla and pour some sauce over it.
Roll the tortillas and place them in a covered baking dish.
Pour the remaining sauce to cover the tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: western pound cake
directions: Have eggs and butter room temperature.
Cream butter; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Sift flour 3 times; add gradually to batter. Add flavorings.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 4 minutes.
Then invert pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut tender pods of okra.
Wash and cut up in iron frying pan with about 5 or 6 tablespoons bacon grease.
Salt to taste and cook until tender.
Stir often to keep from sticking.

title: two pecan pies
directions: Cook at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in bowl.
Melt butter and cheese together in microwave; add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: turkey pilaf
directions: Melt butter in a heavy skillet or saucepan.
Add pecans, celery and mushrooms.
Cook over low heat, turning often, until pecans are toasted.
Add water, bouillon cubes and salt.
Bring to a boil. Then add rice slowly.
Cover and reduce heat; simmer 25 minutes. Add turkey the last 10 minutes of cooking time.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.

title: mom's peanut butter pie
directions: Mix milk and Dream Whip together; can substitute Cool Whip. Beat cheese and sugar until light.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into crust.
Chill 5 to 6 hours before serving.

title: niku jaga
directions: Simmer until potatoes become soft.
Add green peas and turn off heat and serve as soon as peas are hot through.

title: cobblestone bars
directions: Prepare these ingredients:
butter, sugar, eggs, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with marshmallows, nuts or coconut and chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish; add all other ingredients except cheese. Top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: regal gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Generously grease cake pan. Blend all ingredients in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes for a 13 x 9 pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes for 10-inch Bundt pan. When done, lightly brush with melted butter and remove from pan only if using a Bundt pan. Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired, and top with whipped cream. If you make your gingerbread in a 13 x 9 pan, you may like to serve the pieces of cake in half horizontally and filled with whipped topping, sprinkled with powdered sugar. Cake may be baked in a 10 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan for thinner slices. Ideal for a large number of servings. Reduce baking time approximately 10 minutes. Check to avoid over baking.

title: creamy cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and regular sugar together.
Add softened margarine and mix.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for exactly 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: maple squares
directions: Mix flour, sugar and eggs at low speed, then add oil.
Next add maple flavoring.
Spread in small, well-greased, rectangular pan to cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool a few minutes before cutting.
Nice change from brownies.

title: mountain dew apple cobbler
directions: Wrap each section
of apple in a crescent roll and place in lightly greased 13 x 9 dish.
Melt margarine and mix with sugar. Spoon over apples.
Pour Mountain Dew over apples.
(Do not stir.) Sprinkle with cinnamon and pecans.
I use about 3/4 tablespoon cinnamon.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: southern popcorn balls
directions: Combine syrup and sugar in heavy skillet.
I like to use an iron skillet.
Bring to a boil and then reduce to medium high heat.
Cook, stirring often with wooden spoon, until mixture will spin a thread when dripped from the spoon or to a firm ball stage. Pour over the popped corn and stir until well coated.
Butter your hands and carefully form into balls.
Mixture will be hot. Handle it carefully.

title: brandy slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Freeze. When ready to serve, fill a glass with slush and add 7up.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar, oil and water at medium speed.
Add vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients; stir into egg mixture just until moistened.
Stir in sweet potatoes, raisins and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased 5 1/4 x 3 3/4-inch coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool 10 minutes on a wire rack.
Remove from cans.
Cool completely.

title: instant salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Sprinkle dry jello over this; mix well.
Add pineapple and orange sections.
Refrigerate.

title: hush puppies
directions: Stir dry ingredients until well mixed.
Add onion and milk. Mix well.
Drop batter from teaspoon into hot fat or oil.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes until browned on all sides.
Drain well.

title: wheat bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and let set until yeast starts to work.
Add rest of ingredients.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: meat, rice, mushrooms
directions: Line bottom of casserole dish with meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover meat with rice.
Mix mushroom soup with 1 can water and pour over rice.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour. Serve with your choice of vegetables.

title: honey vinaigrette
directions: Combine in a screw-top jar.
Cover and shake.

title: killer salad
directions: Shred lettuce and carrots in food processor or use grater/chopper. Place in large serving bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Toss well.
Keep cold.
Serve cold.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil butter, sugar and milk until 234°.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Fluff.
Mix well and pour into 10 x 14-inch pan.
Cut when cool.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and add in ingredients listed.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate-nut crispies
directions: In
a
quart
saucepan, combine the sugar and syrup. Cook and
stir over medium heat for 5 minutes to dissolve the sugar. Remove
from
heat;
blend in the chunky peanut butter and
the margarine.
Stir
in the rice cereal.
Spread in pan and set aside.
In a heavy saucepan, melt the chocolate pieces over low heat.
Spread on top of peanut butter-cereal mixture. Chill for 1 hour or until the topping is firm.
Cut into bars. Makes 36 bars.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cover.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: coffee drop cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening. Add egg and vanilla. Mix well. Add dry ingredients alternately with coffee. Add raisins and nuts. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet, covered with wax paper. Bake 15 minutes at 400°. Makes 48 to 50 cookies.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Let hamburger balls cook in the juice about 10 minutes. Add all the rest. Salt and pepper to taste. Should be done in 30 minutes.

title: spicy shrimp
directions: Mix butter, green pepper and scallions; saute.
Stir in clam juice.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to coat shrimp.

title: brussels sprouts with mushroom glaze
directions: Soak mushrooms in stock until tender, about 1 hour.
Remove mushrooms; reserve the stock.
If mushroom stems are tough, remove and discard.
Thinly slice mushrooms.
Pour stock into a nonstick frying pan; bring to a boil.
Whisk in lemon juice, mustard and thyme; cook about 3 minutes.
Immediately add mushrooms and Brussels sprouts.
Toss well.
Serves 8.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Beat the sour cream and eggs well.
Add ingredients together.
Beat until smooth.
Put into lightly greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Top with Streusel.

title: turkey stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet or wok, stir-fry turkey in oil over medium-high heat until no longer pink, about 5 to 6 minutes. Remove turkey and keep warm.
Stir-fry the onion, carrot, green pepper and mushrooms until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.

title: egg strata
directions: Grease 10 x 6 x 1 3/4 baking dish or pan. Line bottom of pan with bread slices. Place 1 slice of cheese on top of each slice of bread. Combine the eggs, salt, pepper, onion, bell pepper and skim milk and mix until blended. Pour the mixture over bread and cheese. Fry the bacon until crisp. Set aside until cool and then crumble. Slice the tomato and place 1 slice on each slice of cheese and bread. Crumble bacon over mixture. Cover and chill overnight. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes. Let stand for a few minutes and cut into squares.

title: chili pepper and crab casserole
directions: Drain and seed chili peppers.
Arrange peppers and slices of cheese in layers in a medium-size casserole.
Drain crab meat and arrange over top; do not break up meat.
Top with beaten eggs. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until eggs are set.
Remove from oven, pour tomato sauce over top.
Return to oven and bake until sauce bubbles.

title: crunchy baked potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except for corn flakes and bake in oblong pan one hour at 425°.
Top with corn flakes and bake another 5 or 10 minutes until brown.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup of the shredded cheese, sour cream, pepper, onion powder, reserved liquid and 1/2 can of the onion rings.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onion rings and cheese and bake for 5 minutes longer.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well; let set 2 hours.
Heat to a boil the vinegar and sugar.
Cool completely; pour over drained cucumbers.
Bag and freeze.

title: white frosting
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil and stir until sugar dissolves. In mixing bowl place 2 egg whites. Slowly pour in hot sugar syrup, beating constantly with mixer until stiff peaks form, about 7 minutes. Beat in 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: sour potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until done; peel and cube.
Heat butter and soup together.
Add sour cream, 3/4 c. cheese and onion.
Stir in potatoes.
Put in casserole dish (9 X 13) and top with remaining cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple, add enough water to make one cup.
Heat; put in gelatin and dissolve.
Add cream cheese, mix well and let cool; then add nuts, cherries, pineapple and cold Coke (1 cup).
Put into refrigerator to congeal.

title: frosty fruit cocktail salad
directions: Blend together cheese and sour cream.
Add sugar and grated lemon rind; blend well.
Add fruit cocktail, marshmallows and banana slices.
Freeze in loaf pan; slice.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.
Yields 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil together green chili, squash, celery, onion, oleo and water for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add egg, cracker crumbs and 1 cup cheese.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for
30 to 35 minutes.

title: chinese chop suey cookies(no baking)
directions: Melt chips over hot water, stirring constantly.
Stir in nuts and noodles.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Chill.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat on medium until well blended.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning with flour and flour last.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter all biscuits.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon; put in greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter, brown sugar and water.
Let boil for 2 minutes at medium heat; do not overcook!
Do not let it crystallize.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: parkerhouse rolls
directions: Mix as for Rumford Biscuit (see recipe).
Roll to 1/3-inch thickness; cut with a round or oval cutter and crease in the center with the handle of a case knife (table) first dipped in flour.
Brush 1/2 with melted butter and fold over.
Put on a pan 1/2-inch apart and bake in a quick (about 400°) oven for 15 minutes.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time beating thoroughly after each.
Sift together flour, and baking powder.
To the batter, add milk and flour alternately. Add flavorings and beat well.
Bake in a large greased bundt or tube pan at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash, carrots and onion (sliced).
In separate bowl, mix cream cheese and soup together.
Add squash, carrots and onion.
Melt butter and mix with dressing.
Put 1/2 of dressing in bottom of casserole dish and press down.
Add squash mixture and cover with rest of dressing.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quiche(quick and easy)
directions: Brown sausage.
Mix cheese and sausage with beaten eggs and milk.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix Dream Whip as directed.
Add cream cheese and sugar.
Mix well.
Spread on pretzel crust.
Heat pineapple with juice.
Add jello to pineapple mixture.
Spread on top of cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: butternut squash soup
directions: In a preheated, 400 degree oven, roast the butternut squash with the seasonings, butter and sugar, until soft and browned. Remove from oven and scoop squash from rind.
In a soup pot, heat olive oil and saute onions.
When translucent, add potatoes and squash flesh.
Cover with chicken stock and simmer until potatoes are soft.
Remove from heat and puree with stick blender or in an upright blender.
Return to soup pot and add heavy cream.
Season to taste.
Enjoy!

title: deer sausage
directions: Mix ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cook small patty for a taste test.
Add seasoning or meat to satisfy taste.
Do not add salt!

title: monkey bread
directions: Place 1/2 cup of sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon in a bowl. Cut biscuits into quarters and put pieces into bowl; shake until well coated.
Put dough in a well-greased Bundt pan.
Put one layer of biscuits and one layer of nuts.
Melt margarine, 1 teaspoon of cinnamon and brown sugar in a pan and bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute.
Pour sauce over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn upside down immediately.
Don't cut.
Enjoy!

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet, melt butter; saute onions.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, peppers and 1/2 cup crumbs.
Pour into shallow casserole dish and top with rest of crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: honey sand balls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat together butter, powdered sugar and honey.
Add the rest, mixing thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place 1 1/2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 14 to 16 minutes or until cookies are barely tinged with brown.
While cookies are still warm, roll them in powdered sugar.
Cool.
Roll again in powdered sugar.

title: harvest potatoes
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Spoon into baking dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: ragu no frying chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Dip chicken in egg and then in bread crumbs, coating well. In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, arrange chicken and bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes. Pour sauce over chicken, then top with cheese. Bake for 10 minutes more or until chicken is no longer pink.

title: applesauce chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine applesauce and soda; stir.
Set aside.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs to the shortening and sugar; mix well.
Add applesauce and dry ingredients; mix well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Cook in a 400° oven for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: souper easy quiche
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add soup and cream, mixing well.
Sprinkle cheese, ham and broccoli evenly over pie crust.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Sprinkle with nutmeg (optional).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center is set. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple slices
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Cut in butter as for pie dough. Beat egg yolks. Add sour cream and beat together.
Gradually add to the flour. Work the dough and then roll about 1-inch thick. Divide the dough into 2 parts.

Line pan. Spread cooled pineapple mixture. Cut remaining dough in strips and crisscross over pineapple. Sprinkle chopped nuts and slightly beaten whites of 2 eggs over entire top. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when ready to serve.

title: brenda's pecan pie
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into 10-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until filling sets.

title: summertime cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 350° or until set in the middle.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all together, except the mayonnaise.
Just before serving, stir in the mayonnaise.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together into a bowl.
Mix the egg, milk and butter or margarine.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until the flour is moistened (the batter will be lumpy).
Fry on a hot skillet or griddle (grease very lightly with vegetable spray). Drop the batter by tablespoonfuls or 1/4 cupfuls.
Cook until the top side of the cake is full of bubbles and the underside is nicely browned.
Turn cake over and brown the other side.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir dry ingredients together. Cut in margarine until it resembles corn meal. Combine buttermilk, egg and soda. Add to flour mixture and stir until just moistened. Knead lightly and shape into ball.
Place on flat greased pan. Cut a cross on top to allow for expansion. Brush top with milk.
Bake for 70 minutes.

title: fudge full peanut butter bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine cake mix, peanut butter, butter and eggs.
By hand, stir until dough holds together.
Press 2/3 of dough into bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: peach bread
directions: Preheat oven to
Mix all dry ingredients together. Make a well and
spoon in the oil.
Add eggs and peaches. Mix well.
Pour into
a
greased,
floured
loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown hamburger; set aside.
Sprinkle cornmeal in greased skillet and brown.
Mix all except cheese, onion, peppers and beef together to form batter.
Pour 1/2 batter mixture into skillet.
On top of this add beef.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle with chopped onion and pepper.
Top with remaining batter and bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hot pizza rolls
directions: Split rolls and spread with margarine.
Place 1 slice cheese on each open-faced roll.
Cover with 2/3 of meat sauce.
Sprinkle with meat and mushrooms.
Add onions and olives.
Top with remaining sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place under broiler until rolls are lightly browned and cheese is melted. Serves 4.

title: best-ever casserole
directions: Early in the day, cook the noodles.
Saute the ground round steak in butter.
Stir in the tomato sauce; remove from heat. Combine the remaining ingredients.
In a 2-quart casserole, spread one-half of the noodles.
Cover with the cheese mixture; add the remaining noodles.
Pour 2 tablespoons melted butter over the noodles.
Add the meat mixture, then chill.

title: salmon puff
directions: Combine eggs, milk and soup.
Blend in remaining ingredients and place in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: zesty macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to box directions.
Rinse with cold water until cooled.
Add vegetables.
Toss with dressing.
Chill.

title: skyline dip
directions: Spread French Onion Dip in bottom and up sides of deep dish pie plate.
Add the Skyline Chili and top with cheese.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Crush cookies in blender; reserve 1/8 cup crumbs.
Melt butter; pour over cookie crumbs.
Mix well.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese; gradually add pineapple, 1 cup of pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Mix thoroughly and chill.
Form in ball; chill.
Roll in nuts.

title: dilled potato salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle top with paprika to garnish.
Chill for several hours before serving to enhance flavor.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine evaporated milk, gravy mix, turkey, vegetables and thyme.
Pour into one frozen pie crust.
Break or crumble remaining frozen pie crust into very small pieces.
Toss with shredded cheese.
Sprinkle over top of pie.
Bake in preheated 400° oven on a preheated baking sheet 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter delite dessert
directions: Blend flour and margarine together.
Add chopped nuts.
Press evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together well.
Roll into 1-inch
balls.
Place
on pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop surprise(gravy)
directions: Cut pork chops off the bone into small squares.
Brown in a large skillet in butter.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in mushroom soup and milk; season to taste.
Simmer for 30 to 60 minutes, stirring occasionally so it won't scorch.
Serve over toasted bread or mashed potatoes.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Dump into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Mix sour cream and Hidden Valley dressing.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Mix with pepper and onions.
Combine sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour over beans.
Add salt and pepper; toss lightly.
Chill overnight.
Keeps 2 weeks.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter. Stir in brown sugar and pecans. Spread in bottom of Handi-Pan. Top with pineapple and cherries.
Blend remaining ingredients at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter over fruit in pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. Check cake center with toothpick.

title: jewish cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients except the milk and coconut and bake in a greased jelly roll pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from the oven and spread the milk on top and sprinkle the coconut on top of the milk.
Bake for 15 minutes longer. Ice with chocolate icing.
Cut into small pieces to serve.
Makes 48.

title: eleanor's impossible pie(coconut)
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Process 1/2 minute until mixed. Pour into well-buttered 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
You will have a crust, a custard-type filling and a brown coconut topping.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugars, butter and oil, beat well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Cover with plastic wrap and put in refrigerator over night.
Make into small balls, flatten with fork and bake at 375° for 10 - 12 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix coconut and nuts.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread in nut mixture.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions; pour over nut mixture.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: In a bowl, combine biscuit mix, cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir in eggs just until mixture is moistened.
Fold in zucchini.
For each round, drop 2 tablespoons of mixture in soft butter or margarine; fry 2 to 3 minutes on each side until brown.

title: jello
directions: Take box of Jell-O and put in a bowl.
Put hot water and cold water in the Jell-O.
Dump the fruit in the Jell-O.
Put Jell-O in the refrigerator for 3 hours.

title: monte's favorite banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour once; measure, adding baking powder, soda and salt.
Sift together 3 times.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° for about 30 minutes or until pie doesn't shake.

title: sausage crescent rolls
directions: Brown and drain sausage. Mix with softened cream cheese. Place a spoonful of mixture onto divided crescent rolls and roll up. Bake according to package directions.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Mix drained strawberries juice and water to make 1 cup.
Boil. Dissolve Jell-O.
Mix in mashed bananas, pineapple juice, nuts and strawberries.
Jell slightly.
Pour half of mixture into mold. Spread sour cream.
Pour in other half.
Chill.

title: white pizza
directions: Defrost dough on pizza	pan
with
a
little olive oil, about 2 to 3 hours.
Preheat
oven
at
Work dough onto pan with fingers or flour
lightly
and roll out to form pizza shell. Sprinkle with seasonings
to taste.
Dribble olive oil over top of pizza.
Bake
about
20 minutes.
Great with soups and salads.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until well blended.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add sifted flour, alternating with milk.
Add flavoring. Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: pork chop casserole(duffie's favorite)
directions: Brown pork chops.
Grease baking dish and layer all the ingredients in order
given.
Cover
and
bake
at	450° for 1 hour.
Uncover for last 20 minutes.

title: candied yams
directions: Old bacon meat and collards to take to Homecoming and Birthday dinners.

title: herb baked potatoes
directions: Put all ingredients in large plastic bag.
Shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Place in roasting pan.
Bake 40 minutes or until done at 450°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Wash soup bone thoroughly. Cover with cold water and boil slowly for several hours. Skim off fat and add first 4 vegetables. Cook for 30 minutes. Add the 3 remaining vegetables. Season to taste. Cook 30 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: holiday ribbon ring
directions: Dissolve strawberry jello in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Pour 1 1/2 cups into 6 cup mold.
Chill until set, but not firm, about 15 minutes.
Chill remaining jello in bowl; gradually blend in 1/3 cup sour cream and spoon over jello in mold.
Chill until set, but not firm.
Repeat with lime jello, remaining 2 1/2 cups water and 1/2 cup sour cream, chilling dissolved jello before measuring and pouring into mold.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: venison sauerbraten
directions: Place venison in earthenware bowl or glass baking dish with onions, bay leaves, peppercorns, cloves, berries, salt, vinegar and boiling water; cover tightly.
Refrigerate at least 3 days, turning meat twice a day.
Never pierce meat when turning.
Drain meat, reserving marinade.

title: chicken doritos casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Doritos and 1/2 of cheese. Line Doritos on bottom of casserole dish.
Pour chicken mixture over the Doritos.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: First mix together water and cinnamon.
Next, grease a loaf tin and spread the can of apples evenly on the bottom.
Add the water and cinnamon mixture.
Be sure butter is cold and break up into small particles, then combine flour, sugar and butter until mixture has the consistency of crumbs.
Do not handle too much, just enough to crumble and blend.
Sprinkle evenly on top of apples.
Bake in 450° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: coffee bavarian
directions: Mix crumb and melted margarine; press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until needed.

title: company potato cabbage
directions: Melt shortening in saucepan.
Add cabbage and onions; saute until crispy-tender.
Spoon half vegetables into a 3-quart baking dish.
Add half of the potatoes.
Repeat layers.
Combine flour and salt and stir in broth.
Cook over low heat until it thickens. Pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes about 10 to 12 servings.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Fry hamburger,
onion and green pepper until brown.
Put in the bottom of pan; pour 2 cans of corn over meat.
Then top with mashed potatoes.
Put pats of butter on top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry torte(makes 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: salt water taffy(atlantic city style)
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup thoroughly. Add remaining ingredients, except vanilla. Stir until boiling.
Boil to the hard ball stage and remove from stove. Add vanilla.
Pour on greased plate after bubbling has stopped. When cool enough to handle, pull until light colored. Twist and cut into suitable lengths.

title: festive lasagna
directions: *Season meat with garlic powder and onion salt.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups warm water.
Melt butter; cream with sugar in a large bowl, then add egg.
Add dissolved yeast to creamed mixture, then add flour and stir until well mixed.
Place in airtight bowl and refrigerate.
To cook, drop by spoonfuls into well-greased muffin tins and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: overnight cinnamon buns
directions: Grease Bundt or other fluted cake pan well and coat with some of the chopped nuts.
Break frozen rolls apart and arrange 12 over the nuts.
Sprinkle half the dry pudding mix on top, then sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.
Arrange the remaining 12 rolls in pan and sprinkle with remaining pudding mix and cinnamon.
Scatter remaining nuts on top.
Bring butter and brown sugar to rolling boil in saucepan and pour over rolls.
Cover pan with a damp cloth, then seal with plastic wrap.
Let rise 8 to 12 hours in draft-free place (alternately let rise 24 hours in refrigerator; remove from refrigerator and let stand up to 1 hour at room temperature before baking).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned and cooked through.
Invert immediately onto serving plate and allow rolls to drop free, covered with sauce. Serve warm.
Serves 12.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Combine carrots, raisins and walnuts in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl; stir well and add to carrot mix. Toss gently.

title: grandmama cobb's pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry.
Set aside.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add yolks of eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Then add egg whites and beat.
Add flour and milk alternately, with flour first and last.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Do not open oven for 45 minutes.
One-half cup of coconut may be added, if desired.

title: water chestnut tidbits
directions: Cut water chestnuts in half.
Roll in small strip bacon. Secure with toothpick.
Microwave 2 minutes on High or until bacon is crisp.

title: higbees queen muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients sifted together alternately with milk.
Work quickly, mixing only enough to blend.
Turn into greased muffin tin.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Sear meat in frypan.
Drain off fat. Mix in baking dish with macaroni, onion, tomato soup and water, salt and pepper.
Add mushrooms, if desired. If you need more liquid, you can add tomato sauce.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat mixture of ingredients until smooth.
Holding your finger over bottom of funnel, fill funnel with batter.
Holding funnel as near to hot oil as possible, remove finger and drop batter into 375° oil.
Use circular movement from center outward when pouring batter.
Fry until golden brown.
Dust with 10x sugar.

title: chocolate covered crackers
directions: Spread peanut butter between 2 Ritz crackers.
Melt chocolate almond bark, following directions on box.
Dip crackers, with peanut butter between, in chocolate and lay on wax paper until set.
Also good using light almond bark.

title: mom's blueberry bread
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream shortening until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in eggs, milk, lemon juice and pineapple.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Set aside. In small saucepan over medium heat, melt magarine.
Add garlic, black pepper and paprika.
Mix well.
Remove from heat and brush on chicken breasts.
Place chicken in an ovenproof dish and bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes or until meat has turned white throughout.

title: shrimp salad special
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Add shrimp; cover and bring to boil.
Lower heat; simmer gently until shrimp turn pink (about 5 minutes).
Drain.
Add tarragon vinegar; let stand about 1/2 hour.
Drain thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients; toss lightly.
Chill well.
Serve in lettuce cups; top with mayonnaise.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place meat in baking dish. Add soup. Top with Tater Tots. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Heat butter in skillet; add garlic, onions; cook 2 minutes. Add shrimp; cook over medium heat for 4 minutes (until shrimp is cooked).
Squeeze lemon juice over shrimp, season with salt, pepper; add parsley and top with cheese.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: pastry for 2 crust pies
directions: Put flour in a large mixing bowl.
Cut shortening into flour. Add water to mixture.
Mixture may be flakey; continue mixing with hands until dough can be gathered to form a ball.
Cut dough in half.
Place on floured surface.
Roll out large enough to cover bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan.

title: pizza salad
directions: First, prepare dressing.
Drain the marinade from the artichoke hearts into a small jar with a lid.
Add to the jar the vinegar, oregano, salt and minced garlic.
Place on lid and shake to blend.
Set aside at room temperature if to be used within a few hours or refrigerate until ready to use.

title: stuffed eggplant("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Cut eggplant in half and scoop out the pulp, leaving a shell about 1/4-inch thick.
Chop the eggplant pulp.

title: baked chicken with onion soup
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut up 1/2 stick butter in bottom of pan.
Place cut up chicken on butter.
Pour onion soup mix over chicken.
Cut up 1/2 stick butter over mix.
Cover and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Combine tomato sauce, barbecue sauce and sugar in a small saucepan over medium heat. Heat the mixture until it begins bubble, stirring often, then remove it from the heat. In a large bowl, add all but two tablespoons of the tomato sauce to the meat. Use a large wooden spoon, or your hands to work the sauce into the meat, until it is very well combined. Combine the remaining ingredients with the ground sirloin -- flour, salt, onion powder and ground pepper. Use the wooden spoon or your hands to work the spices and flour into the meat. Load the meat into a loaf pan (preferably a meat loaf pan with two sections which allows the fat to drain, but if you don't have one of those, a regular loaf pan will work). Wrap foil over the pan and place in oven for 30 minutes. After 30 minutes, take the meat loaf from the oven, remove the foil and, if you are not using a meat loaf pan, drain fat. Using a knife, slice the meat loaf all the way through into 8 slices, while it is still in the pan. This will help to cook the center of the meat loaf. Pour the remaining 2 Tbsp. of sauce on top of the meat loaf, in a stream down the center (don't spread the sauce). Place the meat loaf back into the oven, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes or until it is done. Remove and allow to cool for a few minutes before serving.

title: corn fritters
directions: Drain corn; add dry ingredients.
Mix; add eggs.
Cook in deep fry at 350°.
Brown both sides.

title: turkey pie
directions: Brown ground turkey with onion.
Drain.
Put in microwavable bowl.
Top with mushroom soup and green beans.
Peel and cube potatoes.
Cook in water until done.
Mash with nonfat milk and margarine.
Put mashed potatoes on top of mixture.
Cook in microwave for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Cook rice (= 2 cups cooked).
Mix broccoli, rice, Cheez Whiz, soup, onions and celery together in a large bowl while rice and broccoli are still hot so the Cheez Whiz will melt and blend well.
Put all ingredients into an 11 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: In a medium bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring.
Mix well.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff, but not dry.
Gently fold into sweetened condensed milk mixture.
Pour into prepared crust. Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with whipped topping and reserved crumbs before serving.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter and mix together (by hand) the peanut butter, graham crackers and confectioners sugar.
Add chocolate chips. Roll into 1-inch balls. Cool in refrigerator.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cook over medium heat until thick; pour into favorite pie crust.
Chill.
May be served with whipped topping, if desired.

title: aunt deb's chili
directions: Brown meat; pour off grease.
Add onion, garlic, cumin and chili pepper.
Mix and brown.
Add tomatoes, beans and around 3 cans of water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer until done.
Serves 8.

title: chicken filling for buns
directions: Mix well.
Spread on 20 medium buns.
Warm in oven on low heat.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 320°.
Butter and flour a Bundt pan or a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in water; add juice.
Let set until nearly thick, add other ingredients.

title: cheese grits
directions: Add next ingredients in this order:
cheese, butter and eggs last.

title: real cajun red beans and rice
directions: Cook beans and bacon (which has been thinly sliced) in salted water slowly for 45 minutes.
Add vegetables, seasonings and tomato sauce.
Cook slowly another hour.
Stir occasionally.
Fry sausage; set aside, then add to beans and cook another 45 minutes. Cool, but do not refrigerate for an hour or two.
Then, reheat and bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer gently for 30 to 40 minutes.
The important thing is to serve over boiled rice.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a mixer bowl, combine 2 cups of the flour and the yeast.
In a saucepan, heat milk, sugar, oil and 1 1/2 teaspoon salt just until warm; stir constantly.
Add to flour mixture.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in as much of the remaining flour as you can mix in with a spoon.

title: fudgsicle pie
directions: Mix Oreo cookies and margarine real well.
Press in pan evenly and refrigerate.
Leave in refrigerator at least 15 minutes.
Beat milk and pudding mix.
Fold in ice cream.
When crust is ready, pour in the ice cream mixture and freeze.
Top with chocolate whipped cream before serving.
Also it needs to thaw about 10 minutes before serving.

title: hamburger green bean casserole
directions: Saute ground chuck and onion together.
Drain grease.
Add soup plus well drained green beans.
Crumble up beef bouillon cubes.
Add to skillet.
Boil down potatoes.
Pour off water.
Add egg.
Beat with electric mixer.
Potatoes need to be slightly firm.
(May need a touch of water or milk.)
Place skillet ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put mashed potatoes around edge of pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Beat in half the flour and add salt, oil and the rest of the flour.
Mix well. Knead until smooth.
Place in lightly oiled bowl.
Oil bottom, cover, let stand for 1/2 hour.
Place in oiled pan and spread out. Add sauce and cheese.
More options: pepperoni, sausage, broccoli, spinach.

title: pop tarts
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until light.
Beat in eggs until creamy.
Stir in flour and baking powder to make a soft dough. Divide dough into 16 parts.
Roll each to a flattened ball.
Set on plate.
Wrap in plastic.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese, sugar and salt well. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour and beat until smooth along with the flavorings. Bake in a well-greased and floured Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Remove cake from pan. Place upside down onto plate and place in cake server. Close lid and let it sweat until cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with sour cream and mashed bananas.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
May be divided into two smaller pans and baked for 50 minutes or until pick comes out clean.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring butter, cream and sugar to a full boil for 5 minutes. Turn on low heat and add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Stir well and pour into buttered pan.

title: toffee break
directions: In saucepan, bring sugar, salt, butter and water to a boil and continue until hard crack or 300° on candy thermometer.
Add nuts and stir constantly to prevent scorching.
Lightly grease cookie sheet 15 x 10 x 3/4-inches.
Melt candy bars.
Spread toffee mixture on cookie sheet and allow to cool, then spread the melted chocolate bars on top and sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
Stir ingredients together.
Cover; refrigerate 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Serve with crackers or bread.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add milk and melted butter.
Beat until smooth.
Add corn and eggs.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° until firm with knife, about 1 hour.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Combine cake mix, eggs, water, oil and 2 pkg. pudding.
Mix well, about 2 minutes.
Pour batter into a non-stick or greased bundt pan and bake for 10 minutes at 275°, then another 10 minutes at 300°, and then 35 minutes at 325°.
The cake will be done when a knife, pushed into the center comes out clean.
For topping, gradually add 1 pkg. pistachio pudding mix to Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled cake and refrigerate.

title: fried apples
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and keep hot.
Leave about 4 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Fill with sliced, unpeeled apples and brown lightly.
Sprinkle with sugar, 1/2 cup per quart. Cover and cook slowly until tender.
Remove cover to let apples brown and cook off excess juice.
Serve on hot platter with bacon.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave 4 to 5 minutes; drain.
Cut to desired length and set aside.
Saute onion in butter.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz, stirring until melted.
Add the mixture with broccoli, rice and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Mix well.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with remaining 1/2 can French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dianne's disheviled eggs(servings:  12)
directions: Cut the eggs into halves lengthwise.
Remove the yolks to a food processor; process until smooth.
Add the butter, mustard, mayonnaise, salt and pepper; process again until smooth.
Stuff the egg yolk mixture into the egg whites with a spoon.
Press the halves together gently.
Garnish with parsley.
Chill until serving time.
Interesting way to serve traditional deviled eggs.

title: easy bake stuffed chicken breast
directions: Slightly pound cutlets.
Defrost broccoli; cook rice.
Place a layer of rice on cutlet.
Place 1 to 2 spears of broccoli on top of rice.
Roll cutlet closed and dip in seasoned bread crumbs. Close cutlet with toothpick.
Pour cream of broccoli soup over stuffed cutlets and bake at 375° to 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Recipe serves 4 people.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut in 1/4-inch slices.
In a large saucepan over medium heat, cook carrots in a small amount of water until crisp-tender.
Drain and cool.
Place in a 3-quart bowl.
Add green pepper and onion; set aside.
In a medium bowl, whisk tomato soup, sugar, vinegar, oil, mustard, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper until smooth.
Pour over vegetables.
Stir to coat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or up to 3 days, stirring occasionally. Makes 16 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla. Sift flour, measure and sift again with baking powder, soda and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately to creamed mixture.
Chill dough, roll out to board.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake on lightly greased baking sheet in 400° oven 8 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix mustard and vinegar.
Add oil and garlic.
Marinate artichoke hearts in dressing overnight.
Mix dressing and artichokes with cooked pasta and other vegetables.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate kiss peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour with baking soda and salt. Set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter and peanut butter until well blended.
Add granulated sugar and brown sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Stir in flour mixture until well combined. Using a level 1/3 cup for each, shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll each in granulated sugar.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix well and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: grandma fry's banana cake
directions: *Sour milk:
Place 3/4 teaspoon vinegar in 1/2 cup milk to sour.

title: six course dinner in a casserole
directions: Place layers of first 4 ingredients in a buttered casserole seasoning each layer with salt and pepper.
Spread the raw meat over top and cover with the tomatoes.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat across the grain into 3/4-inch slices, then into strips 3 x 1/4-inch.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in a large skillet. Cook and stir mushrooms in butter for about 5 minutes.
Remove mushrooms.

title: easy oven chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and paprika in a paper bag.
Cut chicken up into frying pieces.
Shake chicken in bag.
Melt 1/4 cup butter or 1 stick margarine in a shallow pan at 425° on lower shelf of oven, until slightly hot.
Add chicken in single layer, skin down.
Place on lower shelf of oven and bake 30 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Turn oven down to 375°.
Bake another 30 minutes, until tender.
If you don't like crisp chicken, cover the pan with aluminum foil, adding 1 teaspoon of water.
