Bake until done.

title: kentucky butter cake...to die for!
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and soda; set aside.

Combine buttermilk and 2 teaspoons of vanilla; set aside. Cream 1 cup of butter, gradually add 2 cups sugar, creaming well. Blend in eggs, one at a time, beating well after adding each egg. Combine buttermilk mixture, alternating with the dry flour mixture, into the creamed butter mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Blend well after each addition (preferably with an electric mixer on slow speed).
Turn into a 10-inch tube pan, greased on the bottom, or two 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Bake for 60 to 65 minutes or until cake springs back when touched in the center slightly.
Run a spatula along the edge and stem of pan. Prick cake with a fork.
Pour hot Butter Sauce over the cake (recipe follows).
Cool before removing from the pan.
Just before serving, sprinkle cake with powdered sugar.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Beat first four ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients after sifting together.
Chill.
Roll in balls about size of a quarter.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes and roll in granulated sugar. Makes 4 dozen.

title: christmas salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients for bottom layer.
Allow to set until firm in refrigerator.

title: coconut delight
directions: Crush vanilla wafers with margarine.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Trim off excess fat, wash and salt.
Place in crock-pot (do not add water).
Cook on high until meat begins to cook, turn to low and continue cooking until meat is tender and falls away from bone (8 to 10 hours).
Remove meat from crock-pot, pour grease out of crock-pot.
Remove fat from meat, cut into pieces, return to crock-pot, add barbecue sauce to taste.
Best to layer meat and sauce, and cook on low until hot again, about 45 minutes.

title: jiffy cake
directions: Make Jiffy cake mix and bake 15 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool.
Mix vanilla pudding and fold into cream cheese.
Add pineapple and spread on cake.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: creamy fruit parfait
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl for 2 minutes, until completely dissolved.
Mix cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened. Remove any remaining ice.
Stir in 1/2 of the whipped topping until smooth.
Stir in oranges, pineapple, marshmallows and walnuts or pecans.
Spoon into 8 dessert glasses.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and add additional fruit, if desired.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: purple cow
directions: Chill milk and grape juice.
Let the children measure milk and grape juice and mix with sugar added to taste.
Pour into jars and let children shake until frothy.
Ladle into glasses.
Top with a small scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and cream cheese; add sugar and mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Add flour, a little at a time, and vanilla.

title: stewed "punkin"
directions: Cut and get pumpkin out of shell.
Boil until just done.
Drain water.
Mash and add salt/sugar to taste.
Put into a skillet with bacon drippings.
Stir constantly to keep from burning until browned somewhat.

title: kraut casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except wieners, and mix well.
Pour kraut mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Slash wieners diagonally, but not completely through, and arrange on kraut. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wieners are lightly brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coconut dreams(a fair winner)
directions: Cream butter, sugar and margarine.
Add flour, 1/2 a cup at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Fold in coconut.
Form into two rolls about 2 1/4-inch diameter and roll in wax paper. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cut chicken breasts into bite size pieces and press into rice mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Mince garlic.
Shell and devein shrimp, leaving tails on.
In a large frying pan, melt the butter in the oil over medium-high heat.
Add shrimp and cook, stirring occasionally, until just cooked through, about 5 minutes.
Stir in garlic and cook about 30 seconds.
Remove from heat; add 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, lemon juice and parsley and toss until the shrimp are coated.
Serve immediately.

title: cafe cocoa
directions: Just before serving, in small bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat cream and confectioners sugar until soft peaks form.
Place 1 heaping tablespoon Quik chocolate flavor milk mix in each of 4 coffee mugs or large cups.
Add coffee to fill cups almost full. Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with shredded orange peel. Makes 4 cups or 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions on box.
While warm, punch holes in cake and pour 1 can condensed milk and 1 small jar caramel sauce over it.
When cool, ice with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle Heath bars over top.
Chill.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Cream together the flour and butter.
Add vinegar, boiling water, mustard, sugar, bouillon cube and eggs.
Cook for 10 minutes in double boiler.
Serve hot or cold.

title: tuna and noodles au gratin
directions: Make a white sauce of butter, flour, seasonings, soup and milk.
Add cheese and stir until smooth.
Place flaked tuna in baking dish with part of the sauce, then add noodles and cover with remaining sauce.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Be sure to use all the pepper and paprika as this makes it better than other casseroles.

title: bonnie's chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring to a full boil the oleo, cocoa and water.
Take off stove.
Add sugar, flour, sour milk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.

title: miracle brownies
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add shortening, eggs, vanilla and corn syrup.
Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(I usually double this and bake it in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.)

title: rhubarb fluff
directions: Cook rhubarb
and sugar together until done.
Add jello and mix.
Whip	evaporated
milk and lemon juice and fold into cooled jello/rhubarb mixture.
Use your favorite cookie crust in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.	Pour mixture over crust and refrigerate.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add milk and pudding.
Mix with mixer until thick.
Fold Cool Whip into pudding mix.
Separate cookies and remove filling.
Crush cookies.
Add filling to pudding mixture.

title: sam houston white cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine until soft and light.
Add granulated sugar gradually and continue creaming for several minutes to incorporate as much air as possible.
Mix flour and baking powder and sift three times.
Add extract to milk and water.
Add flour alternately with liquid to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry, and fold immediately into batter, blending thoroughly, but quickly.
Avoid beating.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Mix milk, sugar, vanilla and flour in a container.
Pour all ingredients in a glass dish. Drop peaches into dish.
Cook until golden brown on top.
Add cinnamon (optional).
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: crab cakes
directions: Remove any shell or cartilage from crabmeat.
Place all ingredients (hold off on the oil) in bowl and mix together gently. Mold into cakes and cook in frying pan for 3 minutes on each side with just enough oil to prevent sticking.

title: crock-pot brunswick stew
directions: In large skillet, cook beef and pork. Drain off fat and set aside. Cover chicken with water and cook until tender. Remove chicken from bone and tear into small pieces. (Reserve broth for another use.) Add chicken to beef and pork. Cook slowly until well blended. Put meat in crock-pot. Add tomatoes, corn, catsup, margarine, vinegar, salt and pepper. Mix well. Cook at 300° to 325° (low heat) for 5 or 6 hours.

title: bow ties with sun-dried tomatoes, shrimp and vodka sauce
directions: In saute pan, melt butter; add shrimp.
Chop sun-dried tomatoes, scallions and mushrooms.
Add to shrimp.
Saute until scallions are wilted.
Add vodka and continue cooking 2 minutes. Add heavy cream, salt and pepper.
Cook until cream is warm.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Add cream mixture to pasta. Serve sprinkled with grated cheese.

title: chicken chenault
directions: Lay the chicken breasts on table or countertop and layer the vegetables on top of each cutlet evenly, in the center.
Sprinkle with the minced garlic and then with salt and pepper to taste.

title: party punch
directions: Pour undiluted orange juice into punch bowl along with milk. Mix well with a whisk. Stir in eggnog.

title: veggie pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta in water with olive oil. Drain pasta.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Serve hot or cold.
Tastes great both ways!

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour over chicken parts.
Pat with butter and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Melt cream cheese into soup.
Add Knox gelatine and stir quickly to keep from lumping up.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite-sized pieces. Place in bottom of casserole dish.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift sugar, soda, flour, spices and salt together in a bowl. Add eggs, oil and vanilla, mixing well. Add apples and nuts. Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove cake from oven, place in heavy brown bag immediately, close tightly and let stand until cool. This is delicious.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, melted butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch square pan.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients in given order.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
May need to add a little more flour.

title: chicken mexican delight
directions: Lightly fry tortillas.
Tear and line 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients, except sour cream and 1/2 of cheese.
Pour on tortillas.
Top with sour cream and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes until hot.
Serves 12.

title: apricot bars
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Sift in oats and brown sugar. Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat 2/3 of crumbs into a 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Spread with preserves.
Top with remaining crumbs. Bake about 35 minutes at 375°.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: quick orange punch
directions: Mix orange juice concentrate with 7-Up.
Add orange sherbet just before serving.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Separate broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces; rinse and drain on paper towels.
Mix the mayo, sugar and vinegar and add to the broccoli and cauliflower along with the onion and raisins or olives.
Stir and add the bacon bits.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: baked acorn squash with apples
directions: Cut squash in halves and scoop out seeds.
Place squash in a baking dish.
Fill centers with apples.
Pour a little water into the dish.
Cover and bake at 350° (moderate oven) for 30 minutes or until partly done.
Sprinkle with salt, sugar and nutmeg.
Dot with fat.
Bake, uncovered, about 45 minutes or until the squash is soft.
Makes 4 servings.

title: nut rolls
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cheese.
Add eggs and mix.
Add flour and make dough (place in refrigerator a couple of hours or overnight).
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Melt butter in saucepan and add small amount of milk, then nuts to make a paste. Add cinnamon to taste.
Roll out a ball of dough on sugared surface.
Add paste mixture (small amount).
Roll up and shape like a 1/2 moon.
Place on cookie sheets that have been sprayed. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: asparagus and almond casserole
directions: Add cheese and almonds to the white sauce.
Place asparagus and sauce mixture in alternate layers in casserole.
Dot with butter and cover top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven until crumbs are brown, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: meatballs to can
directions: Make meatballs.
Place on cookie sheet and bake.
Heat mushroom soup with water; pour over meatballs in cans and pressure can.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Melt butter in pan, then mix in pretzels and sugar.
Flatten out.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Cool completely.
Cream together sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip. Spread on pretzel layer.
Mix Jell-O, water and frozen strawberries together.
Let that set a little.
Once slightly set, pour on top of cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken until tender and cut up.
Cook broccoli according to directions on package and drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, spread broccoli.
Over this, put chicken and then spread soup.
Slice Velveeta cheese on top.
Cook for about 30 to 40 minutes, just until cheese melts and it's bubbly.
tags: cream of broccoli soup or broccoli cheese soup

title: apple-sweet potato bake
directions: Arrange sweet potatoes in buttered casserole dish and pour apples over them.
Sprinkle brown sugar, salt and marshmallow pieces over apples.
Top with cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: green beans with potatoes
directions: Wash beans, trim
ends
and
remove strings; break into 2-inch lengths.
Place water,
bacon and beans in a large pot; bring to a boil.
Reduce
heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add
potatoes,
salt
and
pepper.
Stir gently. Cover and cook
20 minutes or until tender.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: cottage pie
directions: Brown beef with onion in large skillet.
Break up meat.
Drain off fat.
Add water.
Bring to a boil.
Add bouillon cubes, salt and pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir until cube is dissolved.
Add frozen vegetables.
Simmer 25 minutes.

title: yams with orange sauce
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes; place in a serving casserole. Mix cornstarch and sugars in saucepan.
Heat remaining ingredients in sugar mixture until thick.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine yeast, 1 teaspoon sugar and enough warm water to dissolve.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Allow to sit in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut in 1 x 3-inch strips.
Dip in 2 sticks of melted oleo.
Layer in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Cover and chill thoroughly. Serves 8 to 10.

title: festive seafood cheese spread
directions: In small mixer bowl beat cream cheese and sour cream at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until smooth (1 to 2 minutes).
If desired, reserve 1/4 cup each Sea Stix and cheese.
Stir in remaining ingredients except crackers.
Cover, refrigerate 2 hours to blend flavors.
Garnish with Sea Stix and cheese.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: top notch pizza bake
directions: Brown hamburger and
onion (peppers and mushrooms can be added too).
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with 1 package crescent rolls. Combine hamburger mixture with sauce and pour over biscuit mix in pan.
Put on cheese (all).
Cover with the other package of crescent rolls.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Blend in Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust. Add pie filling to top.
Chill.

title: pumpkin apple streusel muffins(makes 18 muffins)
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients; set aside. In medium bowl, combine eggs, pumpkin and oil.
Add liquid ingredients to dry; stir just until moistened.
Stir in apples. Spoon batter into greased or paper lined muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.
Sprinkle Streusel Topping over batter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: mother's pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut unpeeled tomatoes into 1/2 inch slices.
Sprinkle slices with salt and pepper.
Let tomatoes stand for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, place milk, flour, eggs and bread crumbs each in separate shallow dishes.
Dip tomato slices first in milk, then flour, then eggs, then bread crumbs (or cornmeal).
In a skillet fry half the coated tomato slices at a time in hot oil over medium heat for 4 to 6 minutes on each side or until brown.
(If tomatoes begin to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium low.)
If necessary, add more oil.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Roll out crackers, add melted butter.
Press in bottom of 8 x 10-inch
pan.
Whip Dream Whip, add cheese and powdered sugar. Spread 1/2 of Dream Whip mix on graham crackers.
Add cherry pie filling.
Spread evenly.
Then top with remaining Dream Whip mix. Chill.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Cook okra in a separate skillet to remove excess liquid. Place okra in a clean skillet. Add all ingredients and let simmer 30 to 40 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar and peanut butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle this mixture into bottom of pie shell, reserving a little to garnish top of pie.
Prepare pudding with milk as directed on package. Pour pudding over sugar-peanut butter mixture.
Top with whipped topping and reserved crumbs.

title: myrtle's zyrtles
directions: Grease 8 x 8-inch pan with butter.
Layer ingredients, starting with crumbs.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden.

title: cole slaw
directions: Place washed and cut lettuce in a blender and chop.
Drain in a colander until excess water is removed.
Add pickle relish and mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package; omit salt.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings.
Add onions to reserved drippings.
Cook until tender. Crumble bacon; reserve 1/3 for garnish.

title: sharon's potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add flour, potato chips and vanilla.
Beat well.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until edges are lightly browned.
Cool 5 minutes on cookie sheets.
Remove to wire rack.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: lemon sponge
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add lemon.
Mix sugar, flour and salt; add to egg mixture.
Stir in melted butter and milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Put in 10-inch pie pan.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: portuguese sweet bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
In large bowl combine flour, salt and nutmeg.
Make a well in center.
Pour in egg and sugar mixture, dissolved yeast, warm water and condensed milk.
Begin mixing with hands and working in butter.
Mix very well.
Dough will be sticky.
Cover and let rise. Turn onto floured board.
Shape into loaf, rolls, etc.
Let rise again. Brush tops with beaten egg. Bake at 325°. Rolls: 15 minutes.
Loaf: 20 to 25 minutes.
Dough can also be used for doughnuts or cinnamon rolls.
Yield:
7 to 8 loaves.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Keep strawberries frozen until ready for use.
Cream margarine, sugar and pretzels.
Press into glass baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: rice dressing(aka dirty rice)
directions: Mix sausage, hamburger meat, green onions and bell pepper. Cook until meat is done.
Add rice and Kitchen Bouquet.
Mix together thoroughly.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook all ingredients about 20 minutes on low heat.

title: molded fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
In saucepan, combine reserved pineapple juice, eggs, sugar and flour.
Cook over low heat until thick (about 5 minutes).
Add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool before adding oranges, bananas, pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: hobo bread
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins and baking soda.
Let cool. Mix well oil, sugar, egg, flour, salt and nuts.
Grease and flour 2 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Fill each half full.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crock-pot ham-n-potatoes
directions: Place half of ham, onion and potatoes in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then cheese; repeat.
Spoon soup over top. Sprinkle paprika on top; cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours.

title: eggnog cakes
directions: Grease and flour 1 large Bundt or 12 small pans.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom.
Heat oven to 350° for small pans or 325° for a large pan.
Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl and beat for 2 minutes.
Fill large pan completely or small pans halfway.
Bake small pans for 20 to 25 minutes or large pan for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes before removing to wire rack.

title: blueberry crust delight
directions: Blend flour and margarine.
Add nuts and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° (it doesn't brown).
Let cool.

title: orange treat cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, substituting 1 1/2 cups whipped topping for the oil or butter.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans about 30 minutes.
Cool in pans on racks 15 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix all ingredients with a spoon until well mixed and waxy or sticky. Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart and press lightly with fork to flatten. Bake for 12-18 minutes. Should be light brown and soft when taken form oven.

title: mush mush cake
directions: Mix above ingredients and spread on cake mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
(You can also use lemon cake mix instead of yellow cake mix.)

title: creamed chipped beef
directions: Saute beef in butter in a large skillet 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in 3 1/2 cups milk; simmer 2 minutes, stirring often.
Combine flour and bouillon granules in a small bowl.
Gradually stir in remaining 1 cup milk.
Gradually stir flour mixture into beef mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt and white pepper.
Spoon mixture into baked puffed pastry shells.
Yields 8 servings.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Stir oleo into hot spaghetti, then stir in Parmesan cheese and well beaten eggs.
Form mixture into a crust in a buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese in the middle.
Cook hamburg and onion in a skillet.
Drain.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Heat. Turn this mixture on top of cottage cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and bake 5 minutes more.

title: creamy texas jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple, evaporated milk, pimentos and nuts.
Pour into flat casserole and chill until thick.
Delicious!

title: chocolate surprises
directions: Combine peanut butter and margarine.
Add sugar until the consistency of thick frosting.
Spread on cracker and put another cracker on top, making a sandwich.
Melt Candi-Quik in double boiler or in microwave until completely melted.
Using a long tined fork, dip each cracker sandwich in chocolate and place on wax paper until dry.

title: hawaiian sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, pineapple and orange juice; mix well. Combine half and half, brown sugar and butter; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until butter is melted.
Add to potato mixture along with salt and cinnamon; blend thoroughly.
Pour into a lightly greased shallow casserole; sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes or until coconut is lightly toasted. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: dennis' boiled lobster
directions: Heat the water and salt to boiling in a Dutch oven.
Plunge lobsters head first into water.
Cover and heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes; drain.

title: hot rolls
directions: Bring oil, sugar and milk to scald.
Let cool.
Dissolve yeast cakes in potato water.
Add eggs.
To mixture flour, salt to liquid in bowl.
Add 2 cups of the flour at a time, using dough hooks.
Mix well.
If all of the flour is not used, put it on the board and work into dough.
Bake at 275° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 2 dozen rolls.

title: oysters italian
directions: Melt butter and crushed garlic.
Shuck oysters and rub each shell with garlic butter; place oyster back in it.
Add salt and pepper.
To the bread crumbs add olive oil, parsley and oregano. Mix carefully and sprinkle over the oysters.
Serve on the half shell.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Mix rice, mushrooms and soup.
Place in pan alternately a layer of the rice mixture, then a layer of pork chops, then another layer of the rice mixture and another layer of the pork chops. Bake at 350° until the chops are done.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion, celery, salt, pepper, allspice and broth. Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Add chopped cabbage.
Stir, cover and cook about 15 minutes or until cabbage is wilted. Stir in 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Pour the mixture into a casserole dish. Top with remaining 1/2 cup bread crumbs. Dot with a little margarine. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Undercook broccoli.
Drain both.
Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Turn into buttered casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Brown beef with chopped peppers and onion.
Add taco seasoning mix per package directions.
Combine tomato sauce, picante sauce and water in bowl.
Pour 1/2 cup into beef mixture; simmer on low heat.
Add 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can Durkee onions.
Stir and remove from heat.
Pour some sauce mixture from bowl into 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Stuff shells with beef mixture and place in dish.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; top with rest of cheese and onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: reimen(cold noodle salad)
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water, then immediately drain and place in ice water until very cold.
Mix dressing ingredients (vinegar, soy sauce, oil, sesame seed, sugar and salt).
Pour over cold noodles and cut vegetables.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Pour milk over bread crumbs; allow to soak until milk is absorbed.
Stir in egg, onion, potatoes and salt.
Heat bacon drippings on griddle or in frying pan.
Drop batter from tablespoon onto griddle and press out rather thin.
Cook slowly, until well browned.
Turn and brown other side.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: ravioli with broccoli sauce
directions: Heat oil on low in medium size saucepan.
Add garlic, salt, pepper and red pepper.
Saute until garlic is lightly browned (5 to 7 minutes).
Add cream and cook 20 minutes to thicken.
Stir occasionally.

title: ham rolls
directions: Chop up onion tips very small. Mix together cream cheese, onion tips and pecans. Spread out mixture onto ham slice. Roll up and cut into bite size pieces. Use toothpicks to hold them in place.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Cut in small pieces.
Mix together chicken, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Mix with melted butter or margarine.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, saute bacon until brown, but not crisp.
Remove bacon and reserve.
Saute onions in drippings until translucent.
Add green peppers; stir and cook about 4 minutes.
Add rice, stirring until rice is coated and turns opaque.
Add tomatoes, ham, reserved bacon, chicken broth, garlic, salt, pepper and thyme.
Pour mixture into large shallow casserole. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until rice is tender.
More broth may be added as casserole bakes.
Add raw shrimp, pushing down in rice.
Cook for additional 10 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter.
Mix together with imitation crabmeat, including juice.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: johnny's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to
Mix all ingredients together to the consistency you
desire.
Place in proper size baking dish and bake for about 1 hour.
Top with ketchup when done.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding into crushed pineapple. Add marshmallows and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip and pour into shallow 8 x 10-inch pan. Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: grandma dear's crumb cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in butter. Remove 1/2 cup of mixture and reserve for topping.
Mix eggs, milk, vanilla and cocoa and add to flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Spread in a greased 8-inch round or 10-inch square pan. Add cinnamon to reserved topping mixture.
Crumble onto cake. Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: king's ranch casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325° for 20 minutes. Melt butter in medium skillet over medium-high heat. Add chopped onions and bell peppers. Saute 8 minutes or until tender. Stir in chopped chicken and next 5 ingredients. Cook, stirring occasionally. Place half of crushed tortilla chips in bottom of 9 x 12 baking pan. Layer with half each of chicken mixture and shredded Cheddar cheese. Repeat layers, ending with cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes or until mixture is thoroughly heated.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour cocoa and butter into mixture; beat until smooth.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in buttered pie pan for 25 minutes.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix and store in jar; add 2 to 3 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: pork and noodle hot dish
directions: Season the pork chops; roll in flour and fry until brown.
Add the soup and water; cook until the meat is tender (about 3/4 hour).
Boil the noodles; drain and add meat, green pepper, pimento, grated cheese and corn.
Mix well.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Will serve about 16.

title: raggedy ann cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured baking pan at 350° until done.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, corn meal, flour, coconut, milk, vanilla and margarine. Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° until thick, about 40 minutes. Put under broiler to brown.

title: janie's easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add onions and saute. Add V-8 juice and kidney beans. Mix together and simmer on low heat for about 15 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi and rice(simple and delicious)
directions: Cut eggplant in 1/2-inch widths.
Sprinkle each piece with salt and let stand in water bath for 1 hour.
Dry each piece.
Brush well with olive oil and bake in 450° oven until light brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all, except 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick salad
directions: Drain the pineapple well.
Combine the cottage cheese, Cool Whip, pineapple chunks, strawberry gelatin (dry from package) and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Chill if desired.

title: sylvia's corn pudding casserole(century old southern recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a casserole dish. Cover and microwave for 5 minutes on High and stir. Cook 11 to 14 minutes on 80% power until almost set. Allow to stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: squash patties
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Mash squash and combine with dry ingredients.
Stir,
combining everything together.
Heat oil and drop heaping Tbsp. of mixture into hot oil.
Turn over, mash down with spoon.
Cook till brown.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Heat broth to boiling.
Blend 1/2 of the flour with the milk. Stir into hot broth and cook until thick and smooth.
Add turkey, peas, carrots, pepper and celery salt.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Cut the shortening into the remaining flour, sifted with the salt.
Stir in beaten egg yolk and water, blended together to form a soft dough.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness and cut to fit top of baking dish.
Pierce opening with fork and brush dough with white of egg.
Bake in 425° oven about 25 minutes.

title: california fettucini
directions: Saute garlic and onions in oil; add basil and saute as well. Add tomatoes (canned and fresh).
Cover and cook on low heat.
Add sausage (browned).
Serve over fettucini.

title: icing
directions: Mix together 1 cup powdered sugar, margarine, salt, flour, Crisco and vanilla; set aside.
Mix together egg white and 1 cup powdered sugar.
Mix both mixtures together.
If not thin enough to spread on cake, add 1 or 2 tablespoons milk.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Stir all ingredients like cake.
Pour into 2 quart baking dish.
Pour 2 cups any type of fruit on top (if using canned or frozen fruit or berries, drain well before using).

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients uncovered for 30 minutes.
Peel, wash and slice eggplant 3/8-inch thick.
Brush slices with oil using a pastry brush.
Fry over medium heat using a Teflon pan until soft, turning once.

title: quick bread
directions: Sift into a very large bowl the biscuit mix, sugar and salt. Soften yeast in milk.
Make sure the milk is only warm, too hot will kill the yeast.
Beat eggs with pinch of cream of tartar until thoroughly broken up.
Combine milk and eggs; pour into dry ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
This is a heavy mixture, so be sure that it is well mixed.
Set aside in a warm place covered with damp dish cloth.
Mixture rises best in 80°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix with rest of ingredients, except stuffing mix.
Make stuffing according to directions on package.
Place stuffing mix on top of chicken.
Put casserole in oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: mother's fluffy chocolate cake
directions: Cream
together brown sugar and shortening.
Add 3 eggs (one at a time).
Mix cocoa with enough water to form a paste. Add flour,
baking soda, and cold water.
Bake in greased and floured pan.
Layers
30 to 35 minutes; 13 x 9-inch pan 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: mock chocolate eclair cake
directions: Make pudding according to box using 2 3/4 c. milk instead. Mix Cool Whip with pudding.
Place crackers on bottom of pan. Pour half of pudding over crackers.
Continue to layer.

title: big chocolate chip cookie
directions: Cream wet ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Form into a huge cookie on greased pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for about 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: Soften steak by pounding until thin.
Cut into 1/4-inch wide strips.
Sprinkle meat with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix above ingredients. Bake at 325° for 40 - 45 minutes.

title: creole skillet beans
directions: Heat oil and butter in skillet. Saute onions and bell pepper until soft but not brown. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Stir to mix well. Cover and cook over low heat for about 10 minutes, stirring as needed.

title: ready to eat pickles
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar; heat, but do not boil.
Mix pickles, onions and peppers.
Sprinkle salt and celery seed over them. Pour sugar and vinegar syrup over mixture.
Mix well; store in large glass jar, covered in refrigerator.

title: fran dewine's caramel corn
directions: Fill a large roasting pan with 6 to 7 quarts popped corn.
In another pan, add brown sugar, margarine and white corn syrup. Boil 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Blend in vanilla, soda and salt.
Pour mixture over popcorn, mixing well.
Place in 250° oven for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally from bottom.
Spread on sheets of waxed paper to cool.
Store airtight.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine
all
ingredients in saucepan.	Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Remove garlic.
Makes approximately 2 cups.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix sour cream and dry instant pudding together.
Add crushed pineapple and mix.
Add marshmallows and pecans if desired.

title: crunchy peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat together butter, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar. Add and beat until light the eggs and vanilla.
Sift together and add to creamed mixture the flour, soda and salt.
Lightly mix in the Shredded Wheat.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, bananas and pecans.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Put in 9 X 13 inch dish.

title: chocolate doughnuts
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and egg.
Add milk and slowly add dry ingredients.
If dough does not seem stiff enough to roll, gradually add small amounts of flour.
Roll on floured surface and cut with doughnut cutter.
Deep-fry in vegetable oil for 2 to 3 minutes, turning once.
Coat with sugar or frosting.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Slice zucchini and pat dry.
Dip in eggs which have been beaten and coat with bread crumbs.
Brown in oil on both sides and drain on paper towels.
Use a 9 inch baking dish.
Spread a layer of the sauce in bottom of dish then a layer of zucchini, then a layer of the cheese and then sauce again.
Repeat with layers until zucchini is used.
Top with more cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In casserole dish, place deboned chicken in bottom.
Next, add all vegetables.
Mix in a separate bowl 1 cup flour and milk. Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until crust is brown.

title: low-fat coconut cream pie
directions: Cook pie crust by directions.
Make pie filling by directions. Add coconut and Equal; top with Cool Whip.
Contains 12 gm fat per serving.

title: quick minestrone soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in pot.
Add enough water to just cover ingredients.
Simmer until cabbage is tender.

title: aunt lodie's chicken pot pie
directions: Debone chicken, discard skin.
Add mixed vegetables to chicken broth and simmer about 30 minutes; add cream of chicken soup, stir until well mixed.
Pour into a 9 x 14-inch baking dish over boned chicken.

title: pea salad
directions: Defrost peas (do not cook).
Place in colander in fridge overnight.
Combine mayo and sour cream.
Add peanuts at serving time on top.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: You can either leave this spread in a bowl or you can chill it.
Form into balls and roll in nuts.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cover chicken with water.
Add salt and onion to water; boil gently until tender.
Remove from bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Place chicken in casserole.
Combine chicken broth, potatoes and carrot and pour over chicken.
Spread can of soup over this.
In a bowl, mix together 1 stick butter, flour and milk.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: sherry's apple streusel
directions: In a large bowl, combine apples with sugar, raisins, 1 teaspoon flour and 2 teaspoons apple pie spice; mix well.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In a medium bowl, combine 2 cups flour, brown sugar, salt and 1 teaspoon apple pie spice; mix well. Add butter and cut into coarse pieces.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 10 minutes; reduce to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Blend milk, lemon juice and egg yolks together and pour in graham cracker pie crust.
Chill in refrigerator, then put Cool Whip topping on top.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Blend the oleo and the cheese.
Add flour, salt, red pepper and Rice Krispies.
Form small balls and press flat with fork onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Boil first four ingredients for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add next three ingredients and beat well. Stir in oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper; let cool.
Serve.

title: spamwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients, except buns, throughly.
Spread on buttered hot dog buns and wrap in foil for oven baking or Saran Wrap for the microwave.
Bake 15 minutes at 325° (preheated) oven. Bake on High in microwave just long enough to heat through. Freeze leftover sandwiches and thaw before baking.
A great sandwich to keep in the freezer for snacks.
Just be careful on that first bite.
It is hot.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Put in saucepan the butter and milk.
Heat until melted.
Add this to egg mixture; beat until well mixed.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle nutmeg on pie before baking.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour (very rich and good).

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Saute meat, onion, bell pepper, seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Line bottom of bowl (casserole dish) with 1 pound Tater Tots and meat mixture.
Mix soups; pour over top.
Add 1 pound Tater Tots on top of mixture.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and casserole is bubbly.
Makes a large casserole.

title: chicken
directions: Grease the pan.
Put in the chicken and place a slice of cheese on top of each.
Put prepared stuffing on top of that. Cover with undiluted soup. Cover with Saran Wrap and microwave on High for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients. Freeze and serve.

title: aunt hazel's spice cake
directions: Boil together for 5 minutes the first 7 ingredients.
Cool, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° in 13 x 9-inch greased and floured cake pan until middle tests done.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in small saucepan (flour, milk and salt).
Heat over low heat until paste forms, stirring constantly until thick.
Set aside to cool.
In mixing bowl, beat the next 4 ingredients with mixer until smooth, about 4 minutes.
Add paste ingredients.
Beat until mixture becomes smooth and light, about 4 more minutes.
Food coloring may be added if color is desired.

title: veg-all stuffed meat loaf
directions: Combine and set aside.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar, water and sugar.
Stir in crushed pineapple.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll into 2 or 3 rolls.
Wrap in aluminum foil with shiny side toward meat.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Punch holes in bottom of rolls with a fork.
Place in rack in baking pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Leave on rack until drained and cool.

title: nappa cabbage salad(10 to 12 servings)
directions: Thinly slice cabbage.
Add onions.
Melt margarine and brown noodles.
Be sure to break noodles in small pieces and do not use packaged noodle seasoning.
When noodles are golden brown, add almonds and sesame seed.
Finish browning, watching carefully. Remove and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
Let cool.
Stir dressing well.
Toss with salad greens and noodle mixture 15 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Add 5 to 6 cans water, salt and pepper.
Add spices and stir well.
Simmer 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain off all drippings.
Add beans, salt and hot sauce and simmer together for 10 minutes.
Cut up lettuce, tomatoes and onion as for a salad, using a large bowl.
Mix in meat mixture.
Add cheese and dressing and toss lightly.
Add crushed tortilla chips last and toss again.
Serve as soon as possible.

title: homemade low cholesterol egg substitute
directions: Separate 1 dozen large eggs, saving whites and discarding all yolks but one.
Add 1 yolk to whites.
Add dry milk and food color.
Blend and store in covered container in refrigerator.
Use within 1 week or freeze part for later use.

title: easy bake cobbler
directions: Mix milk, sugar and flour in bowl until smooth.
Melt butter in a deep pan. Pour in mix, then pour fruit into mix. Bake at 350° to 400° for 30 to 45 minutes or golden brown. Let cool down, then tear it up.
Serve with ice cream.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut shortening into flour. Add liquid and mix lightly with a fork.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Knead gently 1/2 minute.
Roll out dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet in very hot oven at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen biscuits.

title: light bread buns
directions: Note:
Does better baked in greased Pyrex cake dishes.

title: quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Drain and crumble.
Beat eggs, biscuit mix, margarine, milk, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch or bigger pie plate or oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle bacon and cheese over top.
Press gently.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs. Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt; stir into shortening mixture. Chill dough. Roll into balls the size of small walnuts. Roll in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon. Place about 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake until lightly browned, but still soft (8 to 10 minutes) in 400° oven.

title: old fashioned fruitcake
directions: Prepare the first 8 ingredients and sift enough flour over this to coat good (not from the 2 cups).
Then mix your cake batter in a separate bowl, using the rest of the ingredients together.
Add this to the fruit mixture, mixing well.
Bake in a tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours or until done.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Rinse and pick over berries; quarter and core apples.
Quarter oranges, removing center and any seed.
Put through grinder (skins on).
Add sugar to taste; stir until dissolved.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve in orange or grapefruit fluted shells.

title: chicken-a-la-brian
directions: Flatten each breast.
Put pats of butter and garlic on chicken. Fold breast in half; roll in uncooked Stove Top.
Grease baking dish; put rolled breasts in dish.
Put remaining Stove Top on top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: yeast bread - mom's
directions: Dissolve yeast with 2 tablespoons sugar and warm water, set aside.
Mix sugar, oil, warm milk or water; then add yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Add flour slowly, mixing well.
Turn onto floured surface, kneading good until dough holds shape.
Flip into greased bowl until it's greased all over.
Set in warm place to rise double in size. Punch down and make your bread rolls, loaf, 4-leaf clover, knots, braids, etc.
Let rise in warm place.
Bake at 350° until done.
Butter tops.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Dry each slice of ham with paper towel.
Take softened cream cheese and spread on each slice of ham.
Starting from one end, evenly roll ham and place in refrigerator until chilled.
When chilled, slice into pinwheel shapes and serve.

title: raisin-studded meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly, using only about 3/4 of the tomato sauce.
Pack into a greased 3 1/2 x 7 1/4-inch loaf pan.
Spread remaining sauce on top of loaf.
Cook in slow oven at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: never fail divinity
directions: In saucepan, mix corn syrup, sugar, salt and water.
Cook, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking, without stirring, until firm ball stage or 248° on candy thermometer. Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Pour about half the syrup slowly over whites, beating constantly.
Cook remainder until hard ball stage (272°).
Add slowly to first mixture and beat until mixture holds its shape.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by dessert spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: grape salad
directions: Wash and dry grapes. Mix cream cheese and sugar. Blend well. Add sour cream and vanilla. Mix well. Pour over grapes and stir gently until the grapes are coated. Top with sugar and pecans.

title: busy day pie
directions: Drain fruit.
Combine milk and lemon juice.
Mix until thick. Blend in fruit and nuts.
Pour in pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: cherry congealed salad
directions: Mix together well and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain and arrange in 9-inch baking dish.
Boil chicken until done.
Drain and arrange on broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice together; pour over top of broccoli and chicken.
Then top with cheese and crumbs.
Squeeze butter may be put on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolks and mash.
Combine yolks, crab meat, celery, green pepper, salad dressing mix and sour cream, blending well.
Stir until well mixed.
Refill egg whites.
Chill until serving time.
Makes 24 stuffed eggs.

title: jello dream salad
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O in 2 cups water and gel.
In 1 cup hot water, add marshmallows and stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and crushed pineapple.
Let set until cooled.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Combine all this with cooled lemon mixture. Add nuts and pour over congealed lime and return to refrigerator to congeal after lemon Jell-O is completely congealed.
Mix strawberry Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water and 1 cup cold water. Cool completely.
Pour over lemon and return to refrigerator.

title: salad dressing
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients.
Mix last 4 ingredients with cooked ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: chili dip
directions: In a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch microwave pan, spread cream cheese, then spread the chili.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top of the mixture.
Cover and microwave until Mozzarella cheese is melted (about 6 minutes).

title: turkey rolls
directions: Blanch the broccoli for 5 minutes.
Wrap each spear in 1 slice of turkey.
Layer in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Top with Cheddar cheese soup and 2 tablespoons crushed croutons.
Serve with rice.

title: crescent lasagne
directions: Meat Filling:
Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Add onion, garlic, parsley, seasonings, tomato sauce and paste.
Simmer uncovered 5 to 10 minutes or until onion is tender.

title: pecan fudge
directions: Put sugar, butter and milk in a 2-quart saucepan and bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, chocolate, vanilla and pecans.
Beat vigorously. Pour in a buttered oblong pan, cut in squares when cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sauce for leftover meat
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in oil or whatever you prefer.
Add
tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Season with soy sauce and Worcestershire,
add
pepper and whatever spices you desire. Simmer for	about
minutes.
Add
sliced leftover meat and simmer for about 15 minutes more.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cool cake. With fork, put holes in cake.
Pour Kahlua over top of cake and refrigerate overnight.
Mix mousse as directed on package.
Let set in refrigerator.
In food processor or blender, crush candy. Crumble cake.
Mix cake and candy together.
In bottom of a trifle bowl, put half of the cake and candy mixture.
Pour half of mousse over cake, half of the Cool Whip over the mousse and repeat the layers.
Shave chocolate on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine in pan and cook until clear.
Add 3 Tbsp. dry strawberry jello.
Cool.
When cool add 1 quart of cleaned strawberries and pour in cooled, baked pie shell.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Thoroughly mix first 4 ingredients for crust.
Press on bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Sides should be about 1 3/4 inches high (may need to double crust ingredients).

title: tear apart bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
In large bowl, pour boiling water over shortening and dissolve.
Add sugar, salt, eggs, flour and dissolved yeast.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fried bananas
directions: Heat butter over medium heat.
Add bananas.
Stir in syrup and stir until well heated.
Serve with pancakes or egg omelet.
Makes 3 portions.

title: cool fruit salad
directions: Fold in 1 can of Eagle Brand milk and 9 ounces Cool Whip. Chill in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cut into squares and place on lettuce leaf.

title: cranberry-chocolate ice cream
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, cook cranberries and orange juice until cranberries pop, about 8 minutes. Place in food processor or blender; add extract and pulse for about 5 minutes or until coarsely chopped. Freeze 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls.
Melt 1/2 block paraffin wax and 6 ounce pack of semi-sweet chocolate (mini bits) together in pot, then take a toothpick and dip balls in chocolate and place on waxed paper to cool.

title: minute steak and onions
directions: Put salt, pepper and flour on steaks.
Lightly brown on both sides in oil.
Take steak out of skillet; put onion in the pan and brown.
Place steak back in skillet with cup of water to make gravy.

title: fresh blueberry coffee cake
directions: Combine berries, 1/3 cup sugar and cornstarch in a small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until sauce is thickened, stirring constantly.
Set sauce aside.

title: red devil's food cookies
directions: Mix ingredients, then beat 3 egg whites and fold in after adding 1 small bag chocolate chips.
Bake 10 minutes in 375° oven. Cool, then frost with favorite white icing.

title: pasta florentina
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Saute garlic, onion and mushrooms in 3 tablespoons olive oil.
When soft, add tomatoes.
Season with oregano, basil, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Add spinach.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over pasta with grated cheese.

title: dream punch
directions: Whip sherbets and 7-Up until consistency of thick cream.
Serve in punch bowl.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: apple-oat muffins("a healthy breakfast start")
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly oil or spray 12 muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray.
In a bowl, whisk together oats, milk, sugar, corn syrup, oil and egg white.
In another bowl, mix flours, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and nutmeg. Stir apples into flour mixture until evenly distributed.
Stir milk mixture into flour mixture, just until moistened.
Spoon batter into muffin cups.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or
until golden brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: sweet rice
directions: Boil the water.
Add rice and salt. Bring to a boil again until water evaporates (uncovered). Stir occasionally. Add 3 cups milk. Simmer until rice is cooked, about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 1 cup sugar and cook awhile longer.
Place in shallow dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon and refrigerate.

title: onion soup
directions: Simmer beef broth.
Saute sliced onion with butter until soft, not brown.
Stir flour into cooked onions.
Add onion mixture, salt and pepper to broth.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes over medium heat.
Place bread in individual bowls.
Pour soup over bread and cover with Swiss and Parmesan cheese.
Set under broiler for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: quail
directions: Melt butter in heavy frying pan.
Brown quail and remove from pan.
Saute other ingredients, except sherry, for 3 minutes.
Then add the quail and water.
Cook slowly, covered, for 1 1/2 hours. Baste and add a little additional water as needed.
Uncover and add sherry; cook for 30 minutes.
Good served with herb rice.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa and milk to a boil.
Then pour over sugar, a little at a time.
Add vanilla and mix good.
Then spread on cool cake.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix sugar and jello; add hot water and stir until jello is dissolved.	Add pineapple and juice.
Drain oranges and add to mixture.
Add sour cream and stir.	Refrigerate.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding, 1/2 of the Cool Whip and all of the sour cream together until smooth.
In a large, flat bowl or baking pan, place a layer of bananas, then a layer of wafers.
Pour pudding mixture over bananas and wafers.
Repeat until all the bananas, wafers and Cool Whip are used up.
Top with remaining Cool Whip. Sprinkle with pecan pieces, if desired.

title: italian shells
directions: Combine tomato sauce, tomato paste, hamburger, oregano, garlic salt, parsley, onion, water, salt and pepper and simmer in a pan. Cook 1 box of shell macaroni according to package directions. Drain and mix with tomato mixture and pour into a casserole dish. Top with American and Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°, or until hot and bubbly.

title: cracker candy
directions: If you like Heath bars, you'll love these!
Layer saltines on foil lined cookie sheet.
Be sure to use the foil and to use a pan with sides.
In saucepan, melt butter and sugar.
Bring to boil. Cook for 3 minutes.
Spread over crackers.
Bake for 5 minutes in 400° oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and let stand for 5 minutes and then spread.
Cool in refrigerator until hard.

title: whiskey sour slush
directions: Boil tea bags with 2 cups water.
Set aside.
Combine lemonade, orange juice, 7 cups water, sugar and whiskey.
Add tea and freeze overnight.
Spoon into glasses and fill with 7-Up, Sprite, club soda or similar drink.
Leftover slush can be refrozen.
Keeps well.

title: best ever pie crust
directions: Combine egg yolk and vinegar in 1/2 cup; add enough water to fill the 1/2 cup.
Blend Crisco and flour with salt and sugar. Quickly blend with the egg mixture, just enough to get the flour to stick together.

title: tuna touchdown
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Empty soup into a 1 quart casserole. Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Add tuna (or salmon or chicken), 1 cup potato chips and peas to the soup.
Stir well.
Sprinkle top with remaining 1/4 cup potato chips.
Bake for 35 minutes or until heated through.

title: chicken cutlet - tomato supreme
directions: Cut chicken breasts into nugget pieces.
Dip in beaten egg and Italian bread crumbs.
Pan-fry in small amount of olive oil and set aside. Dip zucchini in egg. Pan-fry and set aside.
Saute tomatoes, peppers and wine for 3 to 5 minutes. Add chicken breasts and zucchini.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese. Simmer until bubbly.

title: chewy granola bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine brown sugar, peanut butter, corn syrup, margarine and vanilla; blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Press mixture evenly in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.

title: low-fat turkey burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing turkey last.
Shape into 8 patties.
Coat a nonstick skillet or electric frypan with cooking spray and pan-fry.
Makes 4 servings, 270 calories each.

title: peach pie supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange sliced peaches in pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in cream* and vanilla.
Pour over peaches.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sandy's manicotti
directions: Brown meat with garlic and onion; drain grease.
Combine 2 cups tomato juice, tomato paste, oregano, salt, pepper and sugar with meat.
Stir and simmer while preparing filling.

title: rice salad mold
directions: Cook rice.
Cool.
Cut up other ingredients fairly small (I use food processor).
Combine with rice and mayonnaise.
Pour into a Pam-sprayed mold.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Put ingredients in a 1-quart Tupperware casserole bowl. Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes and stir.
Microwave another minute. Stir and serve.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill 24 hours for best flavor. Serve with rye bread and/or raw vegetables.

title: banana bread (muffins)
directions: In a bowl - combine butter and sugar until well beaten. Add egg and egg whites and vanilla, beat until well beaten. Add mashed bananas, mix well. Combine flour mixture to butter mixture alternately with milk. Add nuts. Mix well. Pour batter into greased loaf pan (9x5x3) or fill muffin tins (lined with muffin papers) 2/3 inch from top. Bake at 350 degrees. Loaf pan - 1 hour and 15 minutes or muffins - 15 to 20 minutes. Bake until browned and toothpick inserted neat center comes out clean. Cool bread in pan on wire rack 10 minutes. Remove from pan. Cool completely. Slice and serve with butter

title: honey oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter with honey and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla. Blend baking soda with flour; add to butter mixture.
Combine coconut, walnuts, raisins and oatmeal; stir into butter-flour mixture.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen one-ounce cookies.

title: balsamic turkey
directions: Combine flour and pepper; coat turkey cutlets with flour. Shake off excess.
In heavy skillet, heat 2 tablespoons olive oil. Add turkey and brown on each side.
Remove to warm platter.
Add remaining oil along with peppers and garlic.
Reduce heat to low and cook until tender.
Add basil and vinegar; return turkey to skillet.
Raise heat to moderate and cook 2 minutes longer until turkey is done.
Calories 250 and fat 12 g.
Serves 4.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain liquid from beans.
Place in bowl.
Mix green pepper and onion.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.
Best fixed the day before serving.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers; remove seeds.
Precook green peppers in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Let cool.

title: brown sugar shortbread
directions: Beat butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
With wooden spoon, stir in flour until smooth.
(Dough will be stiff.) Refrigerate dough, covered, for several hours.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Divide the dough in half.
Roll out dough to 1/3-inch thick.
Using 1 1/2 or 2-inch cookie cutter, cut and place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: new potato salad
directions: With skins on, cut potatoes into bite size pieces.
Spread out on a cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until tender. Stir in all ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a large casserole dish, put some chicken, shredded.
Pour soups and butter mixture over.
Add some crushed crackers, repeating layers, ending with crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread layer of refried beans on large plate.
Add a layer of avocado dip.
Add a layer of cheese.
Top with strip of green onion, tomatoes and black olives.

title: easy icebox cake
directions: Place unwrapped Twinkies and layer in casserole dish or deep bowl.
Pour thawed strawberries over Twinkies.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken normandy
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Place 1/2 of mixture in a greased casserole.
Combine chicken, mayonnaise, onion, celery and salt and put into casserole.
Put remainder of bread crumb mixture on top.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over casserole. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Take casserole out 1 hour before baking time and pour evenly on top the cream of celery or mushroom soup.
Bake, uncovered, 40 minutes at 325°.
Top with grated cheese and put back into oven for just a couple of minutes to melt.

title: roast young stuffed pig
directions: Note:
Must use large commercial oven, 3 x 3-foot.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef with taco mix and onion; let cool.
Mix together remaining ingredients except salad dressing and corn chips.
Combine both mixtures.
Right before serving, prepare salad dressing according to package directions; pour over salad. Break up corn chips over salad; serve.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: In medium bowl beat cream cheese until light and fluffy, add milk and stir in lemon juice and vanilla, pour into pie crust. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with cherry pie filling before serving.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add sugar, eggs and butter.
Fold in oats.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: rose's dressing
directions: Toast bread, then tear into small pieces and put in large bowl, then cut celery and onions in small pieces.
Put in with bread. Put egg in a small bowl; add milk and beat until mixed.
Pour into the bowl with the bread.
Take chicken or turkey and tear into small pieces.
Put in with the other ingredients.
You can cook meat the day before, if desired.
Sprinkle poultry seasoning over ingredients and mix with broth.
Put in a medium pan, greased with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg thoroughly.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and nutmeg.
Stir alternately with milk. Fill greased mini-muffin tins (about 1 3/4-inch size cups) 2/3 full with batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown. Immediately roll in 6 tablespoons melted butter, then in mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Serve warm.
Makes 12.

title: irene's salmon ball
directions: In medium bowl, flake salmon; add cream cheese and mix.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Form into ball, wrap in wax paper and refrigerate.
Place on serving plate and sprinkle with nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Add all other ingredients in order given.
Cook in 2 loaf pans, greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Sometimes I add 1/2 cup chopped nuts, chocolate chips or raisins.

title: vanilla fudge
directions: Cook the first three ingredients for about 6 to 8 minutes over medium heat.
Check for soft ball stage.
Turn off the stove and add the rest of the ingredients quickly.
Blend together well. Pour into a greased pan or dish to cool about half.
When it is set, but not cold put out on waxed paper and cut into pieces.

title: praline bars
directions: Line a 1 x 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Coat pan with margarine or spray with Pam.
Boil margarine and brown sugar for 10 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers and put finely chopped pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Break into bars when cool.
Delicious!

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together and bake until bubbly.
Cover with canned onion rings.
Bake till crispy.

title: pork-and-beef barbecue
directions: In 3 1/2 to 5-quart slow cooker, place beef, pork, onions and peppers.
Thoroughly combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover; cook on high (300°) for 8 hours.
With a wire whisk, stir mixture until meat is shredded.
Serve on hard rolls.
Makes 12 sandwiches.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: You also need 2 (9-inch) cake pans.

title: tortilla chip casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and season as desired.
Add soup and enchilada sauce.
Cook over medium heat until bubbly.
Pour over tortilla chips in a casserole dish.
Spread sour cream over mixture and top with cheese.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk.
Sift flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add wets to well in drys and beat until smooth. Slowly pour 1/2 cup batter into 275° fat for deep frying.
Fry until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Enjoy!

title: hot cocoa
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, salt and water to boil.
Simmer 2 minutes. Stir in milk and heat, but don't boil.
Remove from heat and beat with egg beater.
Serve at once.

title: 60 minute cracked pepper ring
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
In large bowl mix remaining flour, sugar, pepper, salt and yeast.
Stir in hot water and oleo.
Mix in egg and only enough reserved flour to make soft dough.
On floured surface, knead 4 minutes.
Divide dough into 12 pieces; shape into balls.
Arrange in circle in greased 10-inch tube pan.
Cover. Place tube pan in large shallow pan half filled with hottest tap water for 15 minutes.
Beat 1 egg yolk with 1 tablespoon cold water.
Brush on ring.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until done. Remove from pan; cool on wire rack.

title: peach cobbler supreme
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a Dutch oven; set aside until syrup forms.
Bring peach mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook for 10 minutes, or until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter; stir until butter melts.
Roll half of pastry to 1/8-inch thickness; cut into 8-inch square.
Spoon half of peaches into a lightly buttered 8-inch square baking dish.
Top with pastry square.
Bake at 425° for 14 minutes.
Spoon remaining peaches over baked pastry square.
Roll remaining pastry; cut into 1-inch strips.
Arrange in lattice design over peaches.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put chicken and rice in a bowl.
Cook 5 minutes.
Check it 5 times.
Then it is ready and you eat it.

title: fast candy
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave for 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter. Mix completely.
Add Rice Krispies and marshmallows.
Mix well. Pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: bran muffins
directions: Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Mix and keep in refrigerator for 4 to 6 weeks.
Add more flour, if necessary.

title: chewy chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter, sugars and pudding mix. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition. Beat in the vanilla. Gradually add flour and baking soda to the creamed mixture. Stir in the chips and nuts (the dough will be stiff). Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown. Remove to wire racks to cool. (The addition of the pudding makes a big difference.) Serve these with a cold glass of milk and watch them disappear!

title: broccoli cauliflower casserole
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tasty meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk for several minutes.
(If using dehydrated onions, soak in milk, also.)
Mix all ingredients together well.
Form in two individual loaves and place in greased pan.
Cover meat loaves with chili sauce.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes or form in single loaf in 4 3/4 x 8 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Cover with chili sauce and bake 1 hour.

title: songie heini cookies
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Blend in sugar.
Add egg yolk, beating until light.
Blend in flour.
Roll dough into small balls. Dip in egg white and then roll in egg white and finally in chopped nuts.
Place ball on greased cookie sheet.
Make depression in center of each ball.
Bake 5 minutes in slow oven and press down center again.
Continue baking for about 15 minutes longer.
Cool slightly and fill centers with jelly.
Yields approximately 1 dozen cookies.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into buttered loaf pan.
Brown 1/2 cup crumbs in butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: toasty cheese loaf
directions: Cut loaf in half lengthwise horizontally.
Cut each half in 2-inch diagonal slices, cutting to, but not through, bottom crust. Place on baking sheet.
Blend butter and cheese.
Spread between slices and over top.
Bake in hot oven (400°) until cheese is melted and bread is crusty, about 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Put all ingredients in a pot.
Add water at least 1 1/2-inches over beans.
Cover and simmer approximately 6 hours.
Add more water as they cook, if necessary.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: oven fried ritz chicken
directions: Dip chicken in yogurt and roll in cracker crumbs.
Place chicken in casserole dish and bake 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and cook 30 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grandma's pie crust
directions: Pour corn oil and milk into a mixing cup (2 cups or more). Do not mix the liquid together.
Mix flour and salt into bowl, slowly put in the liquid by folding in with a fork.
Put the crust mixture in between wax paper and roll out.
Put in pie pan.

title: confetti cauliflower
directions: Steam cauliflower 8 minutes.
Drain.
Set aside.
Heat oil. Add next 5 ingredients.
Saute 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining 3 ingredients.
Cook 1 minute.
Spoon over cauliflower.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Add corn flakes.
Roll into balls or drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 12 dozen.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and cottage cheese in bowl. Layer half the broccoli, chicken, cheese and sauce in 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Repeat layers.
Melt butter and mix with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of casserole and cook at 350° until bubbly, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash
strawberries.
Bring water and cornstarch to boil in pot with food coloring.
Add sugar.
After boils, add jello and let cool.
Stir in strawberries.
Put in pie shell.
After the pie cools,
add
Cool Whip. (For a sweeter taste sprinkle strawberries with some sugar before making pie.)

title: escalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs slightly in large bowl; stir in remaining ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Pour into ungreased square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Sprinkle crackers evenly over top.
Bake, uncovered, until set and golden brown, about 45 minutes.

title: caramel delight
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
While cake is still hot, punch holes in cake and pour the caramel topping into the holes and on cake.
Cool.
Spread Cool Whip on top of cake.
Crumble candy bar on top for garnish.

title: unfried french fries
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Slice potatoes lengthwise into matchsticks.
Coat baking sheet with 3 sprays of vegetable oil. Combine the egg whites and Cajun spice in a bowl.
Add potatoes and mix to coat.
Pour the coated potatoes onto prepared baking sheet and spread them out into a single layer, leaving a little space between.
Bake on bottom shelf of oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until fries are crispy; turn every 6 to 8 minutes so they brown evenly.
Serves 4.
Only 0.5 grams of fat, only 291 calories per serving.

title: double bean chili
directions: In large pot add olive oil, onion and garlic over medium heat until the onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: wheat muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over muffets and raisins; let cool.
Cream the sugar and shortening and add slightly beaten eggs, buttermilk and baking soda.
Add flour, salt and 40% bran flakes.
Mix well and fold in raisin mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes in greased muffin tins.
Set oven to 400°.
Dough may be kept in fridge for up to 6 weeks.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except orange juice and powdered sugar.
Beat for 2 minutes in large bowl.
Spray two 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Remove from pans and sprinkle with powdered sugar and orange rind while still warm.
Makes 18 servings each (1 fat, 125 calories and 31 mg sodium).

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla. Beat until well blended. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 14-inch baking dish, place can of pineapple and add cherries.
Shake cake mix over fruit, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle coconut over cake mix and top with pecans.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
(This is very good after a barbecue dinner.)

title: cobbler with crust
directions: Mix and pour over hot fruit.
Sweeten and bake until brown at 350°.

title: chicken and pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing mayonnaise, half and half, seasoning, salt and pepper in small bowl; blend well.
Cover, refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding, then add Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well together.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: crab fondue
directions: Combine cheese spread and cream cheese in double boiler or microwave until blended.
Stir well.
Add remaining ingredients; heat until blended and hot.
Serve in fondue pot.
Dip bread cubes in fondue.

title: tofu-rice-zucchini casserole
directions: *Cook the brown rice ahead of time; needs 40 to 45 minutes.

title: vanilla icing (cooked)
directions: Put milk, flour and vanilla in saucepan and cook until thick (like gravy).
Chill.
Mix shortening, sugar and salt together. Beat until smooth.
Beat chilled mixture, then add two mixtures together and beat until smooth.

title: corn-bean casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and place in a buttered 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch pan.
Mix together the crushed crackers, slivered almonds and melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fresh apple nut cake
directions: Preheat
oven to 300°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; set
aside.
Combine
eggs, sugar and oil in bowl; blend well. Gradually
add
flour;
blend
well.
Stir
in walnuts, apples, cinnamon and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake one hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick inserted in
center comes
out
clean.
Cool in pan.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing. Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: ritz chicken
directions: Crush Ritz crackers very fine in food processor or with rolling pin.
Dip chicken pieces in milk, then in cracker crumbs. Place in lightly greased baking pan in one layer.
Dot chicken pieces with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken salad
directions: Simmer chicken until tender.
Remove from broth and let cool. Cut into bite size pieces using very little of the skin.
Place in a large mixing bowl.
Add chopped celery, pickles and eggs.
Add mayonnaise and a little pickle juice to moisten.
Salt to taste. Mix well.
Yields 12 servings.

title: hamburg stroganoff
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Brown hamburg with onions.
Add flour, salt and pepper; saute for 5 minutes.
