Add soup; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Serve over cooked rice or chow mein noodles.
Serves 6.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Heat and stir.
Serve hot with chipsters.

title: stuffed clams
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Fill shells with mixture. Sprinkle with parsley flakes and paprika.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: buttermilk pepper dressing
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with mixed greens.

title: tae-toe hash-egg scramble
directions: In 10
to
12-inch
nonstick skillet, put the vegetable oil, olive oil
and
hash
brown potatoes.
Cook about 15 minutes, covered,
stirring occasionally.
Add onion, bell pepper and tomato;
saute until done.
Add margarine, scrambled eggs, salt, pepper
and
garlic
powder.
Cook
until
eggs are set. With plastic egg
turner,
cut
into 4 sections, turn over and cook until done and sprinkle with cheese (optional).

title: zucchini and kidney bean salad
directions: In a large bowl toss together zucchini, green pepper, onion and kidney beans.
In a small bowl beat together oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss lightly.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Place dish into a deeper dish with some water in it.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and stir together.
Add apples, nuts and oil.
Do not beat with mixer.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: bisquick quiche
directions: In bottom of pie pan or oblong casserole, layer any of the first 8 ingredients listed.
Beat thoroughly or blend milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour over layers in pan.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt, pepper and garlic; cook.
After meat cools, mix all ingredients.
Serve cold.

title: ham cabbage rice
directions: Boil ham bone in water until broth tastes "hammy", about 1 1/2 hours.
Add head of cabbage (quartered).
Cook until tender. Remove and keep warm in another pot.
Add rice to broth (about 2 1/2 cups) and cook until done.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix rice and soups together.
Add 1/2 cup milk or water to make more moist (I use water).
Put in bottom of 14 x 10-inch pan which has been lined with aluminum foil.
Place raw chicken (approximately 8 pieces; I use split breasts) on top of the rice and soup.
Sprinkle one envelope of Lipton onion soup mix over the chicken.
Put double thickness of aluminum foil over top.
Fold foil tightly over edge of pan.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Do not peek or add salt.
Serve with green salad and hot rolls.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Set cream cheese out to soften.
Dice green onions and corned beef.
Mix with soft cream cheese.
Mix together thoroughly.
Roll into ball and serve.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate morsels.
Stir mixture until smooth.
Yields frosting for 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: garlic-cheese grits
directions: Cook grits as directed, using water, milk or a combination. Add cheese and butter. Stir until melted and mixed in. Cool. Combine eggs and milk. Pour into grits mixture. Stir until smooth. Pour all into a buttered 2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes. If desired, dust top with paprika and/or sprinkle with more cheese. Serves 8. Recipe may be doubled by simply doubling each ingredient and baking in 9 x 13 rectangular dish.

title: cabbage and kielbasi fetuccini
directions: Cook and drain noodles according to package.
Meanwhile, melt butter in large skillet.
Add cabbage and onions; cook until soft. Add chopped onions and kielbasi. Cook an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir cabbage mixture into cooked noodles.

title: chicken divine
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet with garlic, onion, carrots, celery and a pinch of oregano.
Saute 10 to 15 minutes on medium-high heat until carrots and celery begin to soften.
Add chicken and pour wine in gradually until the chicken is cooked. Stir in cream of mushroom soup and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, stirring periodically.
Serve over pasta or rice.
Should serve 4.

title: confetti rice
directions: In large saucepan, bring rice, water, pepper and chicken bouillon cubes to a boil.
Then turn down to simmer.
Add carrot, celery, bell pepper, onion and margarine.
Mix and cover.
Cook slow until water is gone and rice is fluffy.

title: florentines
directions: Make a pile of crepes and freeze them for the future.
You can substitute puff pastry shells or chocolate shells if you want to.

title: kay's cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix Bisquick and sugar in bowl. Take 1/3 cup of liquid from the pie filling and mix with 1/3 cup water.
Add to the sugar and Bisquick mixture.
Pour over butter in baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Top with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: cold shrimp salad
directions: Mix rice, shrimp, green pepper, celery, onion and olives and set aside.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, pepper and carrots.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand one hour.
Drain if water accumulates.
Combine other ingredients in pan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes and then cool.
Pour over cabbage mixture and let stand for 3 minutes. Stir well.
Freeze in plastic containers.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Mix all together; shape in loaf.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: fumi salad
directions: Add dressing; toss well.
Crush Ramen noodles (uncooked).
Add to salad; toss again.

title: creamy onion dip
directions: Mix all of the above thoroughly.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour. Serve with your favorite chip or cracker.
Makes about 2/3 cup.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine.
Form into patties and fry until golden brown.
Makes about 9 or 10 patties.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumber and slice very thin.
Combine with remaining ingredients and refrigerate several hours.
To make Japanese-style, add 1/2 teaspoon horseradish and 1/8 teaspoon ground ginger.

title: eggs mcfat free
directions: Combine poached egg with ham on muffin, then cheese.
Grill under broiler until cheese melts.
Top with second slice of muffin.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil eggs and potatoes until potatoes are soft.
Dice in small pieces:
onions, celery and eggs.
Put in large bowl with sweet relish and potatoes.
Add mayo to taste.
Mix well.
Salt and pepper.
Add mustard for color (optional).

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat; add salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Combine meat and spaghetti and add tomato sauce.
Put in lightly greased casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with grated cheese and bake until cheese is melted (about 15 minutes).

title: wonderful rice
directions: Stir all in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan with tight cover over medium heat.
When starts to boil, stir all with fork, cover and simmer for 20 minutes for white rice; 45 minutes for brown rice. Let sit 5 minutes, covered, before serving.
On an electric stove, for white rice, just turn the burner off, but leave the covered pan there after it comes to a boil, for 20 minutes.
Needs no other seasoning and it is a special accompaniment to fish or chicken.

title: barbecued chicken casserole
directions: Coat chicken with flour, mixed with salt.
Brown in lard or shortening.
As pieces are browned, arrange in a casserole.
Saute onion, celery and pepper in melted butter or margarine.
Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken in casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steaks into 2-inch strips about 2 or 3 inches long.
Roll in flour and thoroughly brown in shortening.
Add green pepper, Worcestershire sauce, water, onions, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
You may add more water.
It makes delicious gravy.
Serve it on steaming hot rice or potatoes.
You can made your own version by adding mushrooms, etc.
One half hour before starting, put tenderizer on meat.
Serves 6.

title: cake top lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in medium bowl.
Cut in butter, with pastry blender, until mixture is light and crumbly.
Blend in lemon peel and juice.

title: portuguese bean soup
directions: Slice sausage in 1/2 lengthwise and then in 1/4-inch rounds. Fry sausage; add water to cover.
Add carrots
and potatoes.
Cook for 20 minutes; add tomato sauce, kidney beans, spaghetti and 2 to 3 cups water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 1 hour. Add cabbage; cook for 10 minutes.
Serve.
Serves 6.

title: hawaii wedding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and bake in a 15 x 17-inch cake pan or cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let cool.
Mix pudding and cream cheese with 2 cups milk until smooth. Spread on cooled cake.
Let chill until firm.
Spread 2 cans of crushed pineapple on top of cream cheese mix.
Cover with Cool Whip, then coconut, cherries and nuts.
Keep chilled until ready to serve.

title: alabama cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: "dirt pie"
directions: Pour milk into a medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with a wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Stir 1 cup of the cookies and the "rocks" into pudding mixture.
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle with rest of cookies.
Freeze until firm.
You can decorate with gumdrop flowers.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan crisps
directions: Lay toast rounds or crackers out on a baking sheet.
Spoon bleu cheese dressing on each-not enough to drip over edge. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350 degree for 15 minutes, or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Slice orange slices to float in the hot apple cider.
Serve hot.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Clean chicken.
Squeeze lemon juice over.
Salt and pepper. Mix Dijon mustard, honey, paprika and basil together to make glaze.
Brush the glaze all over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in a heavy 3-quart pan.
Mix and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cook until mixture reaches 285°.
Remove from heat at once.
Stir in peanuts and margarine.
Return to heat, stirring, until mixture reaches 295°.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Stir to blend (fast).
Mixture will foam.
Pour on large buttered baking sheet.
Break in pieces when cold.

title: popeye salad
directions: Combine spinach, onion and salt in salad bowl; mix well. Saute bacon in skillet until crisp.
Stir in vinegar and sugar. Pour over spinach mixture.
Sprinkle with eggs; toss lightly. Serves 4.

title: texas king ranch chicken
directions: Save chicken stock to dip tortillas in as you layer out the ingredients in a baking dish.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: winter fruit salad
directions: *Cortland apples will not discolor.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg yolks.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Alternate flour and milk into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in two (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
This cake can also be baked in a loaf pan.

title: cheesecake a la tina
directions: Place ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer.
Start on low speed, move to medium and finish with about 10 minutes on high speed.

Batter should be smooth and liquid. Grease and lightly flour a 10-inch round 3-inch deep baking pan. Pour batter into pan and bake 1 hour in preheated oven at 350°. Leave cake in oven with door closed for an additional hour after heat is turned off.
Cool on rack and refrigerate for storage. Makes 20 servings.

title: easy caramel pie
directions: Boil Eagle Brand milk on stove.
Make sure water covers cans for 3 hours.
When cans come to a boil, turn down to low or simmer.
After 3 hours, open cans carefully.
Pour into pie crusts.
Top with Cool Whip when pies cool.
Garnish with chocolate morsels or pecans.

title: gotta' have 'em pretzels
directions: Combine salad dressing mix and oil in bowl; mix well.
Pour over pretzels in large baking pan.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: coconut bars
directions: Combine ingredients and blend well.
Pat into ungreased square pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix cooled, drained macaroni with sandwich spread.
Add onion, celery seed and drained peas.
Toss well, but gently.
If not sour enough, add more sandwich spread.
Place in covered plastic or glass container and chill.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine crushed pretzels and melted margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar; mix well.
Add to first layer when it has cooled.
Combine Jell-O, boiling water, strawberries and pineapple. When it begins to thicken, add to second layer.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in casserole dish.
Add crushed crackers, onion and ham.
Mix well.
Add salt, pepper and milk; dot with butter or margarine.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 60 to 70 more minutes or until done.

title: lillian dodge's apple crisp
directions: Peel apples and slice thin.
Fill greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; add water and cinnamon.
Blend rest of ingredients until crumbly in consistency.
Spread over apples and bake uncovered in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Cut potatoes in cubes.
Place in fry skillet and cook with small amount of water (less fat grams) and butter; set aside. Brown turkey burger and onion together.
Cook frozen vegetables in microwave then mix with potatoes and burger.
Scramble eggs in bowl, using water as a substitute for milk. Pour over potato mixture and cook until eggs are done.
Season to taste.

title: red cabbage and currant salad
directions: Coarsely shred the cabbage, about 8 cups.
Stir preserves to mash currants; add to shredded cabbage and stir to coat evenly. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Garnish with curly endive and carrot curls.
Serve with crisp bread.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Alternately add milk, flour and flavoring.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 35 minutes.
Be sure you put cake in cold oven.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken until tender; cook and remove bone.
Boil noodles in broth.
Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in 1 tablespoon of butter until tender.
Add noodles, chicken, mushroom soup, pimentos, chopped vegetables and milk to casserole dish.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup of Bakers chocolate.
Mix all ingredients except powdered sugar and pour in oblong baking dish.
Bake for 40- 50 minutes at 350°.
When cool, ice with grated chocolate and powdered sugar.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Combine flours, baking powder and salt; mix well.
In small bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Add to dry ingredients all at once until moistened.
Spoon into cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Immediately remove from pan to wire rack. Contains 140 calories each.

title: steak casserole
directions: Salt, pepper and roll in flour 4 servings cubed chuck steak. Brown chopped onion.
Brown both sides of steak in frying pan. Place in casserole.
Pour almost all grease from pan with browned, chopped onion over steak.
Pour over steak 1 can mushroom soup mixed with 3/4 cup water.
Then place browned onions on top. Bake, covered, for 2 to 3 hours or until steak is tender at 250° to 300°.

title: squash dish
directions: Cut up squash and onion.
Cook until tender.
Pour off liquid and let cool.
Mix in sour cream, chicken soup and pimentos.
Melt butter and pour over croutons; let set.

title: stars and stripes punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Stir in fruit juices and soda. Mix well.
Chill with ice.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: turkey cheese puffs
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and margarine; beat on medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Add milk; beat until smooth.
Stir in pepper and fold in turkey.
Unroll crescent roll dough and separate into 4 rectangles.

Press perforations to seal. Spoon 1/2 cup turkey mixture on the center of each rectangle. Moisten edges with water; bring the 4 corners together at the center over the filling and pinch together to seal.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breast until done.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° until bubbly in baking dish.

title: holiday pumpkin chiffon pie(diabetic recipe)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water; set aside.
Beat egg yolks lightly; stir in milk, pumpkin, salt and spices.
Blend well. Cook in the top of a double boiler, stirring constantly until thick and smooth, about 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; add gelatin and sweetener.
Stir until dissolved.
Cook; then chill in refrigerator until mixture thickens to a consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Remove from refrigerator.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add sugar gradually to egg whites, beating constantly until stiff and shiny.
Fold carefully but thoroughly into pumpkin mixture.
Turn into pie shell.
Scatter graham cracker crumbs over top.
Chill 8 hours.
Contains 153 calories.
Exchanges:
1 bread, 1 fruit and 1 fat.

title: lacy corn cakes
directions: The skillet must be very hot and the batter thin, so that when you drop the batter from a height into the bacon grease, it will spread, making lace!

title: quick dessert
directions: Cut bananas in circles.
Layer on plate.
Put shredded coconut on top, then put honey on top.
Eat with fork or fingers.
Great for us kids.

title: pimento spread
directions: Cook pimento, sugar, vinegar and onion until thickened.
Cool. Add cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Delicious with Bugles, potato chips or crackers.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Slice and boil carrots until tender; drain carrots. In a 2-quart casserole, layer carrots, then Velveeta. Dot with margarine. Top with crushed crackers. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crusts and freeze.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil; stir constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Take off heat and add vanilla or can add maple flavoring.
Beat in powdered sugar until you can spread it.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put rice in bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour boiling water and salt over rice.
Layer cut-up chicken pieces on top. Spread mushroom soup over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Test for doneness.
Serves 4.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Place into greased casserole dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° on cookie sheet or sheet cake pan.

title: delicious spicy chicken
directions: In medium casserole, put and mix soup and seasoning.
Add raw washed chicken.
Cover and bake in oven (350° for 35 to 45 minutes) or microwave.
Serve sauce over rice or noodles.
Spicy and delicious.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend in blender on high speed until ice is crushed.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cake:
Cook cake according to directions on box adding 1 teaspoon butter flavoring.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain Mexicorn; add bell pepper, cucumbers, onions and mayonnaise.
Cover and chill.
Add tomatoes before serving.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix cheese and margarine until creamy.
Sift dry ingredients together twice.
Add small amount at a time to cheese mixture. Add water about 1/2 through.
After all dry ingredients are added, knead it into soft ball.
Squeeze through cookie press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Store in airtight containers.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Put bread cubes in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cheese and browned sausage.
Beat eggs and add 2 1/2 cups milk and mustard. Pour this mixture over the sausage.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, mix mushroom soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Mix well and pour this mixture over the top and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cold banana soup(phillipines)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until smooth. Chill overnight several hours. Garnish with mint leaves.

title: alouette french cheese chicken
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to directions and set aside. Mix soup, onion dip, mushrooms and chicken.
Put chicken mixture in casserole dish, do not pack.
Sprinkle stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered and 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Rinse rice and drain.
Place in bottom of baking dish. Combine soup, water, broth, onion, garlic, salt and pepper. Place pork chops on rice.
Pour soup mixture over chops.
Bake at 450° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until chops and rice are done.

title: orange ice
directions: Mix sugar and water and boil for 5 minutes.
Then add juice and freeze.

title: cinnamon coffee bars
directions: Beat together shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in coffee.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: kathy's easy pear pie
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, put fruit on bottom.
Sprinkle cake mix, covering fruit.
Sprinkle nuts, covering cake mix. Drizzle butter on top.
Bake for approximately 30 to 45 minutes at 300°.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Add grated cheese, onion, mushrooms, pimentos, mushroom soup, mayonnaise and seasonings; stir until blended.
Spray large casserole dish with spray Pam.
Pour casserole into the dish.
Cover casserole with crushed cracker crumbs; dot with margarine.
Cook for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: pretzel desert
directions: Melt butter and mix with pretzels.
Press into 9x13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 400 degrees.
Remove and let cool.

title: southern pralines
directions: Butter the sides of a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In the saucepan combine sugar, brown sugar and cream.
Cook over medium-high heat to boiling, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon to dissolve sugars.
This should take 6 to 8 minutes.
Avoid splashing mixture on sides of pan.
Carefully clip candy thermometer to pan.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, until thermometer registers 234°, soft ball stage.
Mixture should boil at moderate, steady rate over entire surface.
Reaching soft ball stage should take 16 to 18 minutes.
Remove pan from heat.
Add the butter, but do not stir.
Cool, without stirring to 150°, about 30 minutes. Remove thermometer.
Immediately stir in pecans.
Beat vigorously with the wooden spoon until candy is just beginning to thicken but is still glossy.
This should take 2 to 3 minutes.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a baking sheet lined with waxed paper.
If candy becomes too stiff to drop, stir in a few drops of hot water.
Store tightly covered.
Makes about 36 pralines.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter, cocoa and salt in a saucepan.
Heat to a full boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Beat together and drop by tablespoons on wax paper immediately.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine the lemonade, orange juice, pineapple juice, fruit punch and water.
Add the ginger ale and club soda.
Makes 50 4-oz. servings.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Drain and mix French cut beans and Shoe Peg corn.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Mix cream of celery soup, sour cream and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Pour over beans and corn.
Spread Ritz cracker crumbs over mixture.
Pour melted butter over crackers and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs in large mixer bowl on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally for 1 minute.
Stir in baking mix, cinnamon and raisins.
Pour into greased pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Bake until wooden pick comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.

title: beef roll-ups
directions: Lay small pieces of steak flat and salt and pepper each one. Cut bacon and lay on top of steak.
Top with onions.
Then roll up each piece and secure with toothpicks or tie with string.
Put roast 1 1/2 hours until tender, simmering in the tomatoes and water.

title: bacon-wrapped green beans
directions: Take in your hand about 8 green beans and wrap bacon around the middle (like a cord around logs).
Lay on a cookie sheet. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and season salt.
Bake at 350° until bacon is done on top and bottom.
Very easy and tastes great!

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 1/3 c. sugar & melted butter; press into bottom of 13X9 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes; let cool.
Beat cream cheese, 1/4 c. sugar and milk; add Cool Whip and spoon over crust.
Place in refrigerator.
Stir boiling water into jello until dissolved, add cold water and chill for 1 1/2 hours.
Add strawberries and spoon over cream cheese layer.
Chill for at least 3 hours.

title: marzetti casserole
directions: Brown turkey and add next 5 ingredients.
Add tomatoes and simmer.
Mix cornstarch, soy sauce and sugar and add to turkey mixture.
Simmer on low heat until thickened slightly.
Pour over noodles.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, or cook in a double boiler.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
In a mixing bowl beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Stir in jello and beat until smooth.
Stir in vanilla, oranges, pineapple, soda and pecans.
Chill until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.
Fold in 3/4 of the Cool Whip.
Pour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours or until firm.
Serve with remaining Cool Whip.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Drop whole cabbage into boiling water in a large saucepan. Let stand about 5 minutes, until soft enough to separate the leaves.
Drain until cool enough to handle.
Cut out hard stem and carefully remove leaves, being sure to keep them as whole as possible.
Combine beef, rice, eggs, onion and salt; blend thoroughly.
Place a tablespoonful of mixture in the center of each cabbage leaf.
Roll leaf around meat and tuck in ends.
Place rolls close
together in skillet.
Combine vinegar, sugar, tomato sauce and water to make just enough sauce to cover rolls.
Cover tightly; simmer over low heat for 1 hour.
Remove cover; cook 15 minutes, until sauce is slightly thickened.
Serves 8.

title: company breakfast casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with oil. Put hash browns in the bottom of the pan. Brown sausage or hamburger and crumble over the hash browns.

title: italian-style ground beef
directions: With hands, mix lightly together the beef, water, seasoned salt, black pepper and minced parsley.
Shape into 4 patties, about 3/4-inch thick.
Coat both sides of patties with flour.
Dip into egg, then into crumbs.
Brown quickly in hot oil on both sides in skillet.
Arrange in shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Put a slice of cheese on each patty.
Pour spaghetti sauce over patties.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.
Good served with a green salad and garlic Italian bread or other bread.

title: taco dip in a crock-pot(serves a large crowd)
directions: Cut up cheese; melt down on stove or in microwave.
Add a little bit of milk to thin slightly.
Cook beef; add your seasonings (salt, pepper, garlic, onion powder and chili powder). Drain beef.
Add to melted cheese.
Stir in taco sauce and one envelope of taco seasoning.
If too thick, thin with a little more milk.
Turn crock-pot on high; once it's hot, turn on low.
Serve with taco chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 1 hour and 350°.
Stir 1 time after 15 minutes, then leave alone.

title: chili sauce
directions: Put ingredients in large pan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook on low 1 to 3 hours until thick.
Stir often.
Put in hot jars.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat in hot fat in a pressure pan.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Add water and replace cover.
Set control at 10 and cook 20 minutes after jiggler starts.
Reduce pressure instantly.
Serve with fried cornbread.
A meal in 40 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender and blend well.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch pie pan and bake for 60 minutes at 350° or until set.

title: crisp bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, peppers and whole garlic cloves. Add salt.
Cover with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Remove garlic and combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Fill hot jars to 1/2-inch from top.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
(Start timing when water returns to boiling.)
Makes 8 pints.

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: Slice strawberries or peaches into baked pie shell.
Mix together sugar, cornstarch, water and salt; cook until clear.
Add Jell-O.
Cool and pour over fruit in crust.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine and boil for 3 minutes.
Pour the hot syrup around the dumplings (not over) and bake until done at 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; rinse in cold water.
Add dressing; let stand 1 hour before adding other ingredients.

title: flank steak pot roast(serves 4)
directions: Lay flank steak flat.
Mix the leftover rice with sliced canned spinach (liquid and all).
Sprinkle salt into the rice mixture.
Layer rice mixture on flank steak.
Roll the flank steak into a jelly-roll fashion, then tie with twine in 3 places.
Brown the flank steak in the cooking oil; simmer for approximately 45 minutes, covered.
Add a little water if necessary and keep watching.
Make sure liquid does not burn.
Slice the flank steak into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pinwheel sizes and serve with hot rice, mashed potatoes, etc.
Very delicious and lean!

title: peach ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients; add to freezer.
Finish filling to line with milk.
Yield: 1 gallon.

title: chicken stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cut chicken in half and coat with flour, salt and pepper. Melt butter in large skillet and brown chicken on both sides; remove from skillet.
Add 1 tablespoon flour and broth to skillet and stir.
Cook on low heat for 5 minutes, stirring to loosen brown particles.
Return chicken to skillet, sprinkle with basil, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Arrange cooked broccoli in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish, then chicken on top of this.
Stir mushrooms and sour cream into skillet of broth and heat thoroughly but do not boil.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cola-barbecued chicken
directions: In a skillet, warm ketchup, chicken pieces, then cola.
Cover and cook on low for 30 minutes.
Uncover; turn chicken and cook up to 30 minutes more until done.
Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour in a baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°. At the last 10 minutes of baking, take out and put grated Cheddar cheese on top.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except biscuits, in baking dish.
Top with biscuits.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: it won't last cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; do not beat, just blend.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
(Grease pan generously.)

title: teatime muffins
directions: Grease muffin pans (bottoms only) or line with paper muffin cups.
Makes 36 (1 3/4-inch) muffins.
Fill cups half full.

title: cloud cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff. Gradually add sugar and beat until dissolved. Add remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoon onto foil-lined cookie sheets and put into oven. Turn off oven and leave overnight to dry out. Remove from cookie sheets next day.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Pound chicken breasts to flatten slightly. Combine mustard and wine in shallow dish; stir to blend.
In another shallow dish, combine bread crumbs and cheese; toss to mix.

title: chicken treat
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Coat with flour.
In skillet, cook bacon; drain and crumble.
In bacon drippings, brown chicken slowly on all sides.
Transfer chicken to an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine honey, mustard, curry powder and salt.
Drizzle over chicken and bake 15 minutes more.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Serve with fluffy rice.

title: mary perryman's kraut dumplings
directions: Beat the egg until light.
Add milk and mix.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix dry and wet mixtures to form a heavy batter.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot gravy made of kraut and water.
Cook 15 minutes with lid on.
Don't lift lid until done.

title: picante dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Use a large skillet and bring pineapple and jello to a boil. Remove from heat and cool completely. Add buttermilk and Cool Whip. Put into crusts. Refrigerate. This will usually make 2 pies.

title: key lime cheesecake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; stir well.
Press crumb mixture evenly over bottom and up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes; let cool.

title: best salsa worldwide
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients; blend well.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sour cream, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 - 12 minutes.

title: italiano rotini salad
directions: Prepare rotini according to package; drain.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Make dressing from oil, vinegar and seasonings. Toss dressing with salad.
Cover and chill.

title: cheese cake
directions: Press crumbs into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat remaining ingredients together, except cinnamon, until smooth. Pour batter into pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Then turn off oven and allow cake to stay in oven for 1 more hour.

title: lazy man meatballs
directions: Tear bread into small pieces; soak in milk and add to ground chuck.
Makes 50 to 60 meatballs.
Place in layers in baking dish. Mix soups and pour over.
Bake at 325° for about 2 hours.

title: shoo-fly cupcakes
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together with a pastry blender. Reserve 1/2 to 3/4 cup for topping.
Add last 3 ingredients to crumb mixture.
Mix well with a spoon.
Pour into pan.
Add reserved crumbs on top of each cupcake.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes approximately 20 cupcakes.

title: louise's strawberry pie
directions: Cook jello, cornstarch, sugar and water over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Arrange fresh, sliced strawberries in pie shell and then pour cooled mixture over. Chill.
Serve topped with Cool Whip.

title: light and fluffy milnot cheesecake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and chill until slightly thickened.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and then add gelatin and blend well.
Stiffly whip Milnot and then fold into other mixture, then pour into pan, then sprinkle the top with remaining graham cracker crumbs.

title: sauteed shrimp
directions: Melt butter in nonstick frying pan.
Use enough butter to lightly coat shrimp.
Add shrimp.
Sprinkle with white pepper and garlic salt.
Squeeze lemon over shrimp.
Saute shrimp until they turn pink.

title: hot dog bacon wrap-ups
directions: Cut hot dogs and bacon into thirds.
Wrap bacon around hot dog and secure with toothpick.
Place in jelly roll pan.
Mix dry mustard and brown sugar; sprinkle over wrapped hot dogs.
Marinate for 24 to 36 hours.
Heat in oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.

title: peppermint pears
directions: Drain pear juice in a bowl with candy. Stir and microwave for 3 minutes or until candy is melted.
Pour over pears, refrigerate and eat.

title: excellent gnocchi(servings:  4)
directions: Line bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan with aluminum foil. Generously oil the foil.
Heat milk, salt, nutmeg and pepper in heavy 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat just to simmering. Do not boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low; begin whisking or stirring milk briskly and add semolina in thin steady stream, taking care not to let lumps form.
Cook, stirring frequently, until thick enough for spoon to stand upright and unsupported in center of mixture, 5 to 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to low; continue cooking, stirring constantly, until very thick, about 5 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Add egg yolks, 3/4 cup of the cheese and 2 tablespoons of the butter to semolina mixture; stir until butter is melted and mixture is smooth.
Transfer mixture to prepared pan.
Pat out with spatula to 3/8-inch thick. Refrigerate uncovered until cold, at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 425°.
Turn mixture out of pan onto flat surface; peel off foil. Cut gnocchi out of mixture with 2-inch round cutter.
Arrange gnocchi overlapping in 10-inch shallow flameproof baking dish. Melt remaining 4 tablespoons butter in small saucepan.
Drizzle melted butter over gnocchi; sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake until crisp and golden, 20 to 25 minutes.
Place under broiler about 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; remove stems.
Mix sausage and bread crumbs together.
Place sausage mixture in mushrooms.
Sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven on a cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: weisenborn date pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Beat.
Add milk; beat (little).
Add sifted baking powder, flour and salt.
Add nuts and dates, dusted with flour.

title: appetizer baloney pie
directions: Stack thin slices of baloney (4 or 5) with cream cheese with chives in between slices.
Wrap in foil.
Put in freezer about an hour before serving.
Cut in small bite size and serve with toothpicks.

title: applejacks(cookie)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in egg.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Stir in apples.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Drain fruit and add water to juices to make 1 cup.
Add to Jell-O, then add fruit.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex.
Chill until thick.
Combine sugar, sour cream, cream cheese and vanilla; spread over congealed mixture. Sprinkle pecans on top.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well. Sift dry ingredients.
Add to mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves many.

title: casserole bread(italy)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle yeast over water.
Let stand for several minutes.
Stir to dissolve yeast.
Add sugar, salt, butter, 1/2 cup cheese, oregano and 3 cups flour.
Beat with mixer at low speed until blended.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Beat in remaining flour gradually with wooden spoon. Cover bowl with waxed paper and towel.
Let rise for 45 minutes. Stir down. Beat for 30 seconds or 25 strokes. Turn into lightly greased 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in warm water.
Beat eggs in large mixing bowl.
(Have water, whipping cream and eggs at lukewarm temperature.)
To eggs, add 3/4 cup sugar, salt, water, whipping cream, vanilla, lemon extract, raisins and flour; beat by hand until well blended.
This should be a soft dough; too sticky to knead but stiff to stir.
Turn into greased bowl and cover.
Let rise in warm place until doubled (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Stir down; let rise again.
Divide dough into fourths.
Combine 1 cup sugar and cinnamon; melt butter.
Roll dough on floured board (use enough flour to handle dough); brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle cinnamon-sugar mixture (1/4) over dough.

title: blackout cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour desired cake pans. Melt chocolate over very low heat; set aside and cool.
Place butter and brown sugar in large mixing bowl and using high speed, beat until fluffy.
Sift flour and soda into a second bowl.
Mix eggs and vanilla in a third bowl until blended, then beat into butter mixture just until well blended.
Then beat for 1 minute on medium speed.
Add cooled chocolate to butter mixture, beating on medium speed for 1 minute.
Scrape bowl.
Beat in half of flour on low speed until blended.
Then beat at high speed for 20 seconds more.
Mix in sour cream, just until blended.
Add remaining flour and mix until blended.
Add boiling water, mixing on low speed, just until blended.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cake starts to shrink from the sides of the pan.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove from pans and cool completely before frosting with favorite icing.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add beef, cook slightly.
Add remaining ingredients, simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: cheesy vegetable chowder
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large pot and bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, until vegetables are tender. Remove from heat and add corn. Melt butter in saucepan over low heat. Add flour and blend until smooth. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until mixture has thickened. Add cheese and blend. Add cheese mixture to vegetables and heat, stirring constantly. Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: midnight shift ice cream
directions: This will make 2 gallons of ice cream.

title: ham and cheese pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until knife inserted in middle comes out clean (approximately 1 hour).

title: angel delight icebox cake
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate chips with hot water. Remove from heat and add beaten egg yolks and sugar.
Set aside to cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat whipping cream until stiff.
Fold egg whites and cream together.
Then add to cooled chocolate mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Break angel food cake into small pieces.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour chocolate mixture over cake in pan.
Mix with a fork and spread evenly. Refrigerate overnight.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Defrost hash browns.
Combine hash browns, sour cream, cheese, soup and 1/2 stick butter. Spread into casserole dish. Crush enough corn flakes to cover and combine with 1/2 stick melted butter.
Sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until corn flakes are golden brown.

title: one-minute icing
directions: Combine and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and cool. Beat until creamy.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Peel and cut onion fine.
Cook potato and onion in salt water until tender.
Drain, reserving the liquid (there should be 3 cups).
Add milk to the liquid.
Mash the vegetables and add to the liquid.
Reheat.
Serve piping hot garnished with chopped parsley.
Serves 6.

title: microwave leek and potato with lemon thyme
directions: Arrange the leeks and potatoes in a microwave-proof dish. Sprinkle each layer with salt, pepper and lemon thyme.
Pour over the stock.
Cover loosely and cook on High for 8 to 10 minutes until cooked.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl (do not use mixer), combine all dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, pineapple, bananas and nuts; add vanilla.
Put in greased pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham chowder
directions: In stockpot or soup kettle, cook carrots, celery, onion and potatoes in 5 cups water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Add ham butter, salt and pepper.
Blend flour into milk smoothly; stir into soup.
Heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Turn heat to low and allow to simmer, partially covered, 10 to 20 minutes to develop flavor.
Pour soup into large bowl or soup tureen.
Sprinkle top with paprika and chopped parsley.
Serve with hot garlic bread and a tossed green salad for a complete meal.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Form into a ball. Refrigerate.

title: batter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 cups of lukewarm water.
Add oil, sugar, egg and flour.
Blend by hand.
Place batter in refrigerator until ready to bake.
Spoon into muffin tins about 2/3 full and let rise in warm spot about 1 hour.	Batter will keep in refrigerator for a few days.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot grease.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine all and boil for 1 minute.
Heat to serve.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.
Pour on ice cream dessert.

title: crisp cheese crackers
directions: Combine 1/4 cup sesame seed, flour, salt, red pepper and cheese.
Work in butter and oil, using hands.
Mix until dough holds together.
Roll dough out on lightly floured board.
Cut into small diagonal shapes.
Transfer to cookie sheets.
Brush with eggs.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes, or until golden.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry jellos in boiling water.
Put strawberries and crushed pineapple all in a large bowl.
Let set in refrigerator until it starts to set.
Cut up bananas in this mix.
Beat up whipping cream and sugar or use Dream Whip according to directions. Add pecans or coconut or both.
Mix well and put in pan and put in refrigerator.
Let jell.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Beat margarine and 1 3/4 cups sugar until creamed.
Add eggs one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder and mix in alternately with orange juice and vanilla.
Toss the blueberries with 5 tablespoons sugar and fold into batter.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar when cooled, if desired.

title: crawfish etouffee(smothered crawfish)
directions: Cook in oleo until soft.
Add paprika to make red.
Add tails; cook a few minutes.
Add enough water to cover well.
Cook for about 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients. Stir until well mixed. Bake in greased muffin pans at 450° for 15 minutes. When done, brush with butter.

title: barbecue kielbasa
directions: Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot.
Simmer on low for 2 hours or to desired taste.

title: cutout cookies ... the easy way
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix half of the cake mix (dry), margarine, almond extract and egg in a large bowl until smooth. Stir in remaining cake mix.
Divide dough in halves. Roll each half 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board. Cut into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until edges are light brown, 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet. Cool completely before glazing.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Place 24 rolls in pan.
Sprinkle with pudding mix and brown sugar.
Pour melted butter over top. Sprinkle with nuts and raisins.
Let rise on countertop.
(Takes 6 to 8 hours).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert on plate immediately.
Can put together at bedtime and cook for breakfast rolls!

title: smittie's peach-oatmeal muffins
directions: Drain peaches and cut into small pieces. In a large bowl, stir together sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.

Stir in oats and peaches to coat. Stir together eggs, milk and oil. Add to flour mixture and stir to moisten. Fill 12 greased or lined muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes and tested with skewer for doneness.
Cool 5 minutes.
Turn onto rack.
Serve warm or cold.

title: easy sloppy joes
directions: Fry hamburger and onion in electric skillet; drain fat.
Add soup, catsup and Worcestershire sauce. Simmer 30 minutes and serve on hamburger buns.

title: fried squash balls
directions: Drain squash and add onions, eggs, bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper; mix well.
Shape mixture into balls; roll in additional bread crumbs.
Chill about 6 hours.
Fry in deep, hot grease.

title: tostada dip
directions: Combine and beat the ingredients thoroughly.

Spread mixture on a foil lined 12-inch pizza pan, spread shredded lettuce evenly, add 3 sliced green onions, diced green pepper and 1 small diced tomato. Top it all off with a generous amount of shredded Cheddar cheese. Serve with tostada chips.

title: crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Place mixture in an 11 x 17 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with capers and Old Bay, bake for 35 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Melt butter and mix together with remaining ingredients.
Lay chicken pieces in casserole.
Pour sauce mixture over chicken. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and finish baking about 1/2 hour longer.
Baste occasionally.

title: savory baked chicken
directions: Combine salad dressing, juice and seasonings.
Mix well. Pour over chicken.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Reserve salad dressing mixture; place chicken, skin side up, on rack in baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes, brushing occasionally with salad dressing mixture.
Sprinkle with sesame seed; continue baking 5 minutes or until tender.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: cookie necklaces
directions: Melt chips in small pan on low heat.
Spread this generously on flat side of 4 animal crackers.
Place one pretzel in the coating on each cracker, leaving the top two holes of pretzel open to allow for threading ribbon.
Allow to set.
Repeat for remaining crackers and pretzels.

title: venison roast
directions: Soak roast overnight in salted water.
Remove, dry with paper towel.
Brown in hot oil.
Add onions, cook until soft.
Add garlic, vinegar, broth and bring to boil.
Stir often.
Add potatoes and carrots, reduce heat, simmer about 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: deep dish apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: french lemon bars
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, butter and powdered sugar until crumbly. Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Lightly beat eggs.
Mix remaining ingredients together; add to eggs.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool; cut into bars. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: no cook ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
The secret is use fresh milk and don't let one drop of water near the mix.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in order listed (except for bacon) in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover and refrigerate.
Do not toss.
Do not add bacon until serving time.
It will soften if added early.
You can make this the day before.

title: coconut pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given and mix well.
Pour in well-greased 10-inch glass pie pan and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 300° until golden brown.

title: quick apple punch
directions: Combine apple cider, cranberry juice and lemon juice.
Add chilled ginger ale just before serving.
Add crushed ice to tall glasses.
Fill with punch and serve immediately.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Add balance of ingredients and refrigerate.

title: kitchen kasserole
directions: Brown hamburger and add celery and onions.
Simmer until all is done.
Add 2 cans soup and simmer a bit longer.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Place pineapple and orange Jell-O in saucepan.
Allow to come to a boil and then cool.
Combine cooled mixture with Cool Whip and buttermilk.
Spread in rectangular glass dish.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: For one 8-inch cream pie, use same ingredients except use only 2 egg whites and 4 tablespoons sugar.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Combine and beat until blended, then beat 4 minutes.
Pour into two greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Prepare pastry.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pastry-lined pie plate.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour egg mixture into pie plate.
Cook, uncovered, in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.
Cook, uncovered, until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, about 30 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Yields 6 servings.

title: assyrian baked rice(serves 4)
directions: Cover rice with cold water and salt.
Soak overnight. Boil 3 quarts of cold water.
Drain soaked rice and add to fast boiling water.
Boil 5 to 7 minutes or until one grain of rice tastes half-cooked, but not soft.
Pour rice into colander and rinse with cold water.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Use some of the butter for bottom of roasting pan with cover.
Pour rice over butter.
Add remaining butter.
Cover and bake 45 minutes, shaking roasting pan twice during baking to mix butter with rice.

title: bacon and cheddar chicken
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, then drain and crumble.
Discard all but three tablespoons drippings from skillet.
Reserve skillet and bacon.
Dip chicken first into egg, then into breadcrumbs to coat completely.
Saute in hot bacon drippings for 4 to 5 minutes over medium-high heat until golden brown on both sides.
When chicken is nearly cooked, top with cheese.
Cover and melt cheese, then remove skillet.
Crumble bacon over chicken.

title: hermits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Cream shortening, sugar and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, blending well. Add raisins and walnuts; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut meat into small cubes (1/2 inch).
Put into a large pot with
2 tablespoons vegetable oil.	Add salt and pepper to taste. Start
this
cooking
as
you prepare vegetables.
Cut vegetables into
small
pieces.
When they are ready, add the tomato sauce to the meat.
Add vegetables and enough water to cover everything well.
Stir, cover and cook about 2 hours at a low boil.
Stir occasionally.

title: ultimate double chocolate brownies
directions: In a large bowl, combine cocoa and baking soda.
Blend in 1/3 cup melted butter. Add boiling water. Stir until well blended. Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining butter.
Add flour, vanilla and salt. Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pot de creme
directions: Place all ingredients, except cream, in blender and blend until chocolate chips are fine.
Heat cream to boiling point and add, blending again, until chips are dissolved.
Pour into dessert cups and chill.
Remove from refrigerator 10 minutes before serving.

title: date loaf
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in heavy large saucepan.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add dates.
Beat by hand until cool.
Add nuts. Roll into long roll in damp cloth.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Slice 1/2 to 3/8-inch thick.
Makes two logs totaling 26-inches in length.
Makes 50 to 70 slices.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Mix well and freeze.
Add 3 tablespoons mixture to 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 jigger of rum and top with Cool Whip.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Place 9 squares white bark in microwave dish; partially soften.
Add chocolate chips and melt thoroughly in microwave. Add peanuts and mix.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Leave to set.
It takes 1 to 2 hours.
Place in candy tins and store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: puppy chow party mix
directions: Combine chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter in large saucepan.
Mix well.
Stir in Rice Chex; coat well with mixture.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients except soda.
Add egg and milk.
Let stand overnight.
The next morning, add soda and hot water. Grease griddle.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti 8 to 11 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Drain.
Mix in 4 ounces of Italian dressing.
Add green pepper, onion, tomato and cucumber.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons Salad Supreme and paprika.
Stir
all ingredients. Add more dressing and Salad Supreme to taste.
Add paprika for color.
Sprinkle Salad Supreme on top.
Chill before serving.

title: anna lou satterfield's cherry pudding
directions: Mix 1
cup
sugar, milk, flour, baking powder, salt and butter; pour
in
buttered pan.
Pour
cherries over top.
Dot with pieces of
butter then pour over juice and enough boiling water to make 2 cups.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peach coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Mix 2/3 c. dry cake mix, brown sugar, pecans and margarine until crumbly, set aside.
Beat eggs slightly with fork.
Blend in sour cream.
Mix in remaining cake mix.
Batter will be thick and slightly lumpy.
Spread 1/2 batter into pan.
Top with 1/2 of the peaches and sprinkle with 1/2 the brown sugar mixture.
Spoon and gently spread remaining batter over brown sugar layer.
Top with peaches and sprinkle remaining brown sugar mixture on top.
Bake for 55-60 minutes.

title: colonel muncy's oven fried chicken
directions: Coat liver with flour and salt to taste.
Arrange in single layer in baking pan.
Pour undiluted onion soup over liver. Cover; bake in a 350° oven until no pink color shows.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute green peppers, tomato and chilies in the oil; put aside. Bring milk and flour to a boil, turn heat to low and slowly add the grated cheese until melted.
Stir in the vegetables.
Makes 3 to 4 cups.

title: appetizer frittata
directions: In a 10-inch oven going skillet, cook celery and onion in butter or margarine until tender.
Combine eggs, sour cream and cheese.
Chop half the pepperoni and add to egg mixture.
Preheat broiler.
Pour egg mixture into skillet and cook over medium heat, lifting edges occasionally to allow uncooked portion to flow underneath.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes or until almost set.
Arrange rest of pepperoni around the edge.
Broil 5 inches from heat 1 to 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with green onion, if desired.
Cut in wedges.

title: meat quiche
directions: Sprinkle meat into uncooked pie crust.
Cover with cheese, then onion.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over ingredients in pie crust.
Bake at 400° for approximately 15 minutes, until golden brown.

title: cheese-bacon olive spread
directions: Combine ingredients.
If necessary, add a little cream until of spreading consistency.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and baking powder together.
Then mix potatoes in mixture. Add beaten eggs, Karo, melted butter or margarine and milk. Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake about 55 minutes at 375° or 400° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: lime dill dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar and shake well.
Refrigerate.

title: cupcake cheese cakes
directions: Beat eggs, cream cheese and sugar.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Fill cupcakes and bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes (or 5 minutes longer).
In cake pan, bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: diabetic holiday cake
directions: Drain fruit cocktail. Reserve liquid. Add enough water to reserved liquid to measure 2 cups. Combine raisins with liquid in saucepan. Cook until liquid evaporates. Stir in Equal, butter and applesauce. Let cool and pour into large bowl. Add eggs, vanilla, spices and flour. Stir in fruit cocktail and pecans. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 375° for about one hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix vinegar with buttermilk and add dry ingredients.
Alternate with milk.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together and drain off the fat. Add the Rotels and Velveeta, melt together and serve with favorite chips.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Mix together catsup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar. Add mixture to pork and beans.
Add ground beef.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook pork sausage in 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, until well browned, stirring frequently.

title: apple crisp
directions: Beat egg and put in with bisquick sugar and cinnamon.
spread over apples and dot with butter.
Bake 350° for 25 minutes.

title: meat balls(frikadeller)
directions: Mix the first six ingredients thoroughly.
Add eggs, milk and margarine.
Form into 8 patties and fry in butter until brown. Turn down the heat and cover for 30 minutes to thoroughly cook. Serve cold sliced on rye bread or warm with a potato salad.

title: magic meat loaf(crock-pot)
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes in large bowl.
Shape into loaf.
Place in crock-pot.
Cut unpeeled potatoes and place in pot at sides of meat loaf.
Cover and cook on low 10 hours or high, 3 1/2 to 5 hours.

title: a pasta salad
directions: Cook your spaghetti; drain and let it cool.
Put spaghetti in a bowl.
Add chopped olives (drained).
Chop up cucumber and add. Chop up some green onion and add.
Take small bottle of Italian dressing and pour over spaghetti.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a greased and floured 9 X 13 pan.
Mix cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle over batter.
Top with rest of batter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Remove from over and prick cake with fork tines and pour glaze over cake. Best served warm.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix peach preserves, soy sauce and barbecue sauce and pour over browned chicken.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: prayer bars
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa, powdered sugar, egg, vanilla, walnuts, graham crackers and coconut.
Mix and press into cake pan.

title: salsa dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease bottom of casserole dish.
Place chicken in dish.
Mix soups and sour cream well.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Crush crackers and mix with melted butter. Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix shortening, eggs, milk and sugar in bowl (on low mixer). Then add salt, lemon rind, baking powder and flour until mixed. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Bake in loaf pan.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: Combine potatoes, milk, margarine, sugar, egg and salt, mixing well.
Pour
into 1 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top
with
marshmallows and pecans;
broil until marshmallows are lightly brown.

title: floating island
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually beat in 6 tablespoons sugar; beat until stiff.
Bring milk to a boil with salt, vanilla and remaining 1/4 cup of sugar in a saucepan.
Drop meringue mixture by tablespoon into milk and poach the island until they are firm, turning them to cook on both sides.
Remove with a slotted spoon.

title: new england corny clam chowder
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, saute onion in oleo until soft, but not brown.
Add broth, potatoes, seasonings and clams.
Cook, covered, 15 to 20 minutes.
Add corn and milk.
Heat through.
For richer soup, use 1 cup half and half in place of milk.
Serves 4 or 6.

title: baked eggs in potatoes(overall timing: 2 hours)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Scrub and dry the potatoes and push a metal skewer lengthwise through each one.
Place on a baking sheet and rub a little of the butter on the skins.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours. Remove from the oven.
Increase the temperature to 450°.
Cut a slice lengthwise off each potato and scoop out the insides, leaving a shell about 1/2 inch thick.
Mash the scooped out potato (plus any from the lids) in a bowl with remaining butter and seasoning. Beat the cheese into potato mixture.
Press the mixture back into the potato shells, leaving a hollow in the center large enough for an egg.
Place on baking sheet.
Carefully break an egg into each potato.
Season and spoon the cream over.
Return to the oven and bake 8 to 10 minutes, until the eggs are lightly set.
Sprinkle the chives over and serve hot.
Enjoy!

title: quick fresh peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and milk; mix well and pour over butter.
Do not stir. Combine peaches and remaining 1 cup sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to boil and pour over batter; do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until browned as desired.

title: margarita
directions: Rub lime around rim of each glass and dip rim of glass into salt to coat.
Squeeze juice of lime wedge into each glass.
Mix tequila, Triple Sec, sweet-and-sour mix and brown sugar in a blender with ice.
Strain and serve.
Yields 1 drink.

title: "big lank" red beans
directions: Soak red beans in large boiler for 24 hours.
Pour water off beans after 12 hours.
Replace with clean water.
Soak for 12 hours.
Cut hot links into 1-inch.
Combine all ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Cook slow to medium for 4 hours on stove top. Remove boiler from heat.
Remove stew meat from boiler.
Separate strings of beef.
Return beef to boiler.
Return boiler to heat. Cook for 1 hour or until water has thickened.

title: cabbage salad
directions: First Layer:
1/2 head lettuce, chopped fine.

title: red bell pepper over cheese
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients together for 15 minutes.
Keep it in the refrigerator overnight.
Serve over cream cheese.
Eat with crackers.

title: greek rice pudding
directions: Add rice to boiling salted water; cook until water is absorbed.
Add hot milk; cook slowly for about 30 minutes.
Add sugar; heat until dissolved.
Remove pan from heat.
Beat eggs separately in a bowl; add a little of the hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Add butter; stir until melted and blended.
Pour this slowly into rice mixture, stirring constantly.
Replace pan on heat; stir until creamy.
Thickens in 5 to 10 minutes.
Add vanilla; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cool.
Serves 6.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Drain blueberries and pineapple and measure liquids. Add enough water to make 1 cup and add to gelatin mixture. Stir in the drained blueberries and pineapple. Pour into 2-quart flat dish. Cover and refrigerate until firm.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Add butter to boiling water; stir to melt butter.
In a bowl, beat egg and sugar.
Add to water mix; stir.
Add cranberries, nuts, flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda; stir and spoon into a buttered loaf pan (9 x 5-inch).
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: pumpkin cookies with penuche frosting
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to cream mixture. Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: potato refrigerator dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt and shortening, eggs, potatoes and 4 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth. Mix in enough of the remaining flour to make dough easy to handle. Turn dough onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and turn greased side up.
Cover bowl tightly and refrigerate at least 8 hours or until ready to use.
Punch dough down.
Make small rolls and let rise for 1 1/2 hours before baking.
Bake rolls 15 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Bake until golden brown.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill two hours and top with whipped cream.

title: date coconut squares
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan. Add sugar, dates (chopped) and egg and mix well. Cooking over medium heat, stir constantly until mixture boils. Let boil about 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add nuts and vanilla and mix. Add Rice Krispies and mix well. Spread mixture in a pan, 8 x 8-inches which has been greased and lined with half of the coconut. Sprinkle other half of coconut on top and press down lightly. Let cool. Cut into small squares.

title: dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Chill at least one day before serving.

title: quick supper muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Some small lumps will remain.
Spoon batter in 6 large muffin cups which have been coated with non-stick cooking spray. Bake at 350° until risen and golden brown, about 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 6 muffins.

title: kristi's meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients, cheese last.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: nanny's fruit cobbler
directions: Melt one stick of butter (or 1/2 cup butter) in a deep baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and milk into a thin batter.
Pour batter in on melted butter.
(Do not stir!), then pour canned fruit Comstock pie filling on top of batter butter (do not stir!) and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
It should be brown and crispy.

title: dig deep salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in a serving bowl.
Spread mayonnaise over mixture.
Do not stir!
Sprinkle with cheese and cover.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Before serving, garnish with sliced eggs, bacon and tomatoes.
Serves 14 to 16.

title: french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a mixing bowl. Beat with mixer. Refrigerate and use.
Makes 3/4 quart.

title: quick bean soup
directions: Cut up leftover pork into small pieces.
Add water, onions and marjoram.
Bring to a boil, then add baked beans and salt.
Boil 1 to 1 1/2 hours slowly.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients (unsalted or salted crackers may be used). Roll in thumb shaped rolls and fry in hot, deep fat (corn oil or vegetable oil).
Drain.
(Salt, pepper and chopped onion are optional.)

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter, corn syrup, salt and baking soda. Melt in microwave.
Pour melted mixture over popcorn.
Stir well and put in microwave for 2 minutes (Medium-high).
Stir 2 more minutes in microwave.
Stir 1 to 2 more minutes in microwave. Spread out on buttered cookie sheet to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 c pecans.
Chill.
Form mixture into a ball.
Roll in remaining pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onion until onion is tender.
Add salt, pepper, beans and soup.
Put into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Wash potatoes; add milk, egg, salt and pepper.
Spoon in mounds over beef mixture, making a circle.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: boiled icing
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water; stir to mix good.
Cook to 242° or very firm ball stage.
Pour slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites while beating constantly.
Flavor and beat until cool and stiff enough to stand.

title: candy crackers
directions: Line a large cookie sheet with foil.
Lay crackers side by side to cover foil.
In small pan, bring the butter and sugar to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers and gently cover.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let melt and spread gently.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.
Store in cookie tin.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender and dice.
Place chicken in a baking dish.
Add onion and 1 can cream of celery soup.
Mix 1 bag of Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix with broth to moisten.
Pour over melted butter.
Sprinkle with more dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let the sausage and cheese set out until at room temperature. Add biscuit mix, a little at a time.
Roll into 70 balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Blend the crackers, butter and powdered sugar.
Pat down in greased pan to form crust.
Beat eggs; add sugar and cream cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Mix lemon juice with blueberry mixture; spread on crust.
Keep in refrigerator at least 8 hours.
One hour before serving, cover with whipped cream or topping.

title: kentucky hash(biscuits and gravy)
directions: Brown pork sausage and onion.
Drain.
Add mushrooms, soup and milk.
Add eggs.
Serve over baked biscuits.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soup, together in a bowl.
Make into balls and place in dish or pan.
Pour soup over meat balls. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: brownies(strong cocoa flavor!)
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add butter and blend thoroughly.
At low speed, mix in flour and cocoa. Stir in nuts. Spread into greased 8-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 25 to 27 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef in oil with onion, garlic and parsley; drain well. Add tomato paste, water, salt and pepper; simmer for 1 hour.
Cook lasagna as directed on package; mix together eggs and cottage cheese.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, spread about 1/2 cup sauce; alternate layers of lasagna and sauce.
Add a layer of cottage cheese and egg mixture and Mozzarella until dish is filled. Top with sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken liver pate with port and figs
directions: Begin by preparing the figs.
Slice each fig in thirds; let marinate in the Tawny Port for 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour until a thick paste; add pinch of salt and set aside to cool.
Cream sugar, Crisco and margarine until fluffy.
Add flour mixture and vanilla.
Beat at high until ready for spreading.
After icing cake, place cake in refrigerator (covered) until served.

title: super casserole
directions: Layer in order in casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 90 minutes.
Last 15 minutes, top with shredded Cheddar cheese to cover.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Fold dry ingredients into creamed shortening, white sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: jackie's cheese roll
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and roll in chopped pecans.

title: crepe paper clay
directions: Let the torn paper soak in water overnight.
Then drain off the water and mix in the flour.
Knead like dough.
Mold the mixture into shape.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and reserve 2 cups broth.	Chop or shred chicken and place in bottom of baking dish.
Melt butter and pour over chicken.
Drain Veg-All and spread over chicken.
Sift flour and mix with milk.
Pour over chicken and vegies.
Heat soup and broth to boiling point and pour over all.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and let sit for 5-10 minutes to thicken.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Break up cooked chicken in sizes of quarters; place on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix milk with two soups; pour over chicken.
Add 1 cup broth to stuffing and place on top.
Break small pieces of oleo and lay them on top of the stuffing.
Add mushrooms on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade bailey's irish cream
directions: In blender, combine all the ingredients.
Blend until mixed well.
Serve cold.
Stores up to two weeks in the fridge.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add water, vinegar and eggs.
Boil until thick.
Thin with either sour or sweet cream.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Drain beans. Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Place sliced onions over beans.
Make a melted sauce out of next 5 ingredients. Pour over beans and onions.
Add bacon, cut in quarters.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes.
You have to taste to appreciate.

title: mini quiche
directions: Grease muffin tin.
Split rolls in 1/2 roll until flat.
Put in tin.
Add shrimp.
Beat remaining ingredients.
Put 2 teaspoons in each tin.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: tang pie
directions: Combine Tang and milk until dissolved.
Add sour cream.
Let set a few minutes.
Fold in Cool-Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Garnish with mandarin oranges and cherries if desired.
Freeze.

title: aunt rosie's apple cake
directions: Peel, pare and chop apples.
Mix with 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Beat eggs, sugar and shortening until light. Add flour, salt and powder.
Gradually add milk.
Add apple mixture and fold until mixed.
Pour into a 10 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of 3 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Put everything in mixer bowl and mix well. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake on cookie sheet until browned.

title: asparagus-pea casserole(good)
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Make layers of next four ingredients. Add mushroom soup and milk. Cover with cracker crumbs and use remaining butter on top.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; add shortening and eggs and blend. Add water.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Mix 2 minutes.
Bake in large greased and floured loaf pan (5 x 5 x 3-inch) at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Mix soups together with mayonnaise.
Add broccoli and cheese. Put in Pyrex casserole.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: german chocolate chess squares
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl until dry ingredients are moistened.	Press into bottom of a grease 9x13x2 pan.
Set aside

title: bishop's chocolate pie
directions: Mix all, except Cool Whip and vanilla, together in a bowl. Beat until light and fluffy; at least 5 minutes.
Fold in 2 cups Cool Whip and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Pour into cooled pie crust. Chill for several hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Place oil, mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt, and pepper in a medium bowl.
Whisk until blended.
Gently stir in macaroni, tuna, celery, and carrot until well coated.
Mound in center of platter. If desired, garnish with slices of tomato and zucchini or cucumber around outer edge of platter.
Cover and chill before serving.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour in order in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach balls
