directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well in strainer.
Squeeze to remove excess moisture.
Combine rest of the ingredients with spinach.
Shape into balls.
Can be baked now or frozen.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom of pan. Arrange rolls over pecans.
Sprinkle with pudding.
Melt margarine.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over rolls.
Cover with foil overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: marinated mushrooms and artichoke hearts
directions: Cook artichokes until just tender and drain. Slice mushrooms in half through the stems. Combine with artichokes. Combine water with vinegar, oil, garlic, salt, pepper and herbs.
Add vegetables and toss lightly.
Refrigerate, covered. Stir occasionally.
Leave overnight.
Drain before serving.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat together and pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 425° for first 5 minutes, then at 350° until done.

title: sour cream oatmeal cookies
directions: In a bowl, cream together the butter, sugar, eggs and sour cream. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush wafers and pour milk over them.
Let stand while you cream sugar, butter, egg (adding one at a time), vanilla wafer crumbs and coconut.
Pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 275° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: butterfinger torte
directions: Break cake into bite-sized pieces.
Spread half into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the butter, powdered sugar and eggs.
Add the whipped cream and blend together.
Spread half of this mixture on the cake pieces in the pan.
Sprinkle half of the crushed Butterfingers on top.
Repeat this process using the remaining ingredients.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles by boiling, uncovered, stirring occasionally, just until tender, 7 to 10 minutes or as directed on package.
Return drained noodles to kettle; stir in tuna, sour cream, milk, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Pour into an ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and butter. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake about 10 minutes or until heated.

title: old world style beef stew
directions: Cook bacon until half done; drain excess fat.
Saute onions with bacon until transparent.
Add beef and saute until all red is gone.
Add minced garlic and flour until all flour is absorbed. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Mix well, being careful that nothing sticks to bottom of pan.
Reduce heat and let simmer 45 to 60 minutes until meat is tender or bake in 350° oven for 1 hour until meat is tender.

title: mrs. pusey's date pudding
directions: Mix together 1/2 pound chopped dates, soda and 1 cup boiling water.
Add sugar, egg, butter, flour and baking powder.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together 2/3 cup boiling water, sugar, 1/2 pound dates and chopped nuts.
Boil until thick.
Put on top of pudding after baked.
Cut into squares and serve with Cool Whip.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs until hard-boiled, 10 minutes.
Cool eggs by running cold water over eggs.
After eggs are cool enough to touch, crack shells gently and let them soak in cold water.

title: pear pickles
directions: Quarter and core pears.
Boil 20 minutes in clear water.
Boil sugar, water, vinegar and spices (tied in bag) for 10 minutes. Add pears and let stand overnight.
Cook pears until tender and put into hot jars.
Cook syrup until thick.
Pour over pears and seal jars.

title: jello dessert
directions: Crumble angel food cake in a bowl with a lid.
Mix Jell-O according to directions and pour over cake.
Be sure all of cake is covered.
Gel for several hours in refrigerator.
Slice and serve topped with Cool Whip.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients together and cook on High for 4 minutes.
Stir and cook 4 more minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla; stir and cook 2 more minutes.
Remove from microwave and add soda, stirring quickly.
Pour quickly on greased cookie sheet until cool.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: chocolate walnut sour cream cake(makes one 10-inch cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch tube pan.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Fold in walnuts.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: chinese noodle casserole
directions: Brown the onion in small amount of fat.
Mix and brown ground beef.
Drain the fat.
Add water chestnuts, mushrooms, chicken soup, salt, pepper and Accent to taste.
Simmer slowly until done and add sour cream just before serving.
Stir until hot through. Serve over Chinese noodles.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil on high, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cook to a soft ball stage (236°), or until a small amount dropped into cool water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; beat or stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square dish.

title: k.a. baby back ribs barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Salt, pepper, onion salt, celery salt and garlic salt both sides of ribs (1/2 rack of baby back ribs per person).
Bathe ribs in sauce and cook upside down first on grill; turn ribs and add more garlic salt and brush with sauce.
Serve with 2 napkins.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cook
the
sugar
cookie dough according to directions. Let it cool completely.
While cooking the cookie dough, place your cream cheese in a bowl and let it get soft.
If it is the soft
cream cheese,
just
add that and the marshmallow cream together and mix well.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place layer of broccoli in buttered pan. Layer chicken on top. Mix soup, mayo, evaporated milk and cheese and pour over. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, brown sugar, butter and flour and make into crumbs. Remove 3/4 cup for the topping.
To remaining crumbs, add buttermilk, baking soda and beaten eggs.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach pops
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into 10 freezer pop molds. Freeze until hard.
Has 45 calories.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain excess fat.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Add spices, tomato sauce, mushrooms and pepperoni.
Stir.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain noodles; wash with cold water.
Drain again and add to skillet. Warm, then add 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Warm for 1 minute.
Pour into 2 (9 x 13-inch) greased baking dishes.
Divide sliced olives and lay on top of both dishes.
Cover each with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake both dishes or freeze 1 unbaked. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beverly egg cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until they start to thicken.
Add vanilla and gradually add sugar.
When mixture becomes creamy, add food coloring of your choice.
Add in chocolate chips with a spoon.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper-covered cookie sheet before putting in oven.
Turn oven off. Oven must be hot but no longer heating.
Can be decorated most any color for all holidays. Children love them.

title: fudge sheet cake
directions: Mix together sugar, soda, flour and cinnamon.
Bring to boil oleo, cocoa, Crisco and water and pour over dry mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch or larger pan.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking dish sprayed with nonstick spray.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix all together.
Cool until slightly thick.
Pour 1/2 into oblong dish.
Cool until hard.
Spread 1/2 pint sour cream over top and pour other half of jello mixture over the top.
Chill until firm.

title: caramel pecan cake
directions: Mix cake according to package instructions.
Before baking, add the canned caramel pecan frosting, coconut and nuts.
Mix well. Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: german style hot potato salad
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces and fry, not too brown.
Remove bacon from grease and add to potatoes, onions, parsley and celery. To the bacon grease, add flour, salt, pepper, vinegar, sugar and water and heat to boiling point.
Pour over potato mixture and mix well.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Alternate flour and sour cream (in thirds).
Add the baking soda to the last 1/3 of flour.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in a large Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: denise's stir-fry
directions: Marinate sliced meat in soy sauce.
Stir-fry vegetables in hot oil.
Remove vegetables from pan.
Stir-fry meat in pan, then add vegetables again together with meat.
Mix cornstarch with 1 cup water and add to meat and vegetables.
Cook and stir until everything is coated with gloss of cornstarch.
Serves 8.

title: carrot ring
directions: Cook carrots and onions together; drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Butter or Pam a ring mold.
Pour carrot mixture into mold.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Let set 5 minutes.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Pretty with center filled with peas when served.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Put in baking dish.
Thicken gravy and pour over chicken.
Mix ingredients for dumplings and roll dumplings out with a rolling pin.
Cut dumplings into squares and place over chicken.
Bake until dumplings are golden brown.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: In a bowl, combine all the ingredients.
Serve with beef. Makes 3/4 cup.

title: peach crumble
directions: Arrange peach slices in greased shallow baking pan.
Blend remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes; serve warm or cold.

title: lollypops
directions: Will also need candy molds and sticks.

title: the christmas treat
directions: Place crackers in large bowl and sprinkle with garlic salt, dill, oil and dressing mix.
Mix well; cover and let stand for 3 hours before serving.

title: tomato fritters
directions: Mix
ingredients
into
tomatoes and fry brown in a hot skillet of grease.
Makes 8 fritters.

title: pea soup plus
directions: About 2 hours before serving:
In Dutch oven or large kettle over high heat, heat pork butt, split peas, carrots, onion, celery and 2 quarts of water to boiling.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Cover potatoes with cold water; refrigerate overnight.
In a large kettle, melt butter; add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk and cream. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Drain potatoes; place in eight 3-quart baking pans.
Add onions.
Pour the sauce over and stir gently.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours and 15 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Yields 70 to 80 servings.

title: party mix
directions: Melt margarine in pan; add all seasonings. Add all the cereals, nuts and pretzels in a large pan. Pour 1/4 margarine mixture over and stir well. Bake in 200° oven 30 minutes. Remove from oven and pour 1/4 mixture over cereal mix and stir well. Bake 30 minutes. Remove from oven and pour the remaining mixture over the cereal mix. Pour remaining mixture over the cereal mixture; stir and bake 1 hour.

title: salsa mexicana
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Make sure the salsa does not taste like sugar.
Chill in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes before serving to allow the flavors to combine. Serve with tortilla chips or grilled meats.
(Wonderful with chicken breast.)

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg white very stiff.
Add rest of ingredients except pecans.
Then coat pecans with mixture.
Place on bake sheet. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
When cool, break apart.
Store in airtight container.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit, but save pineapple juice.
Mix Tang with pineapple juice; stir well.
Add bananas (sliced) to juice and Tang; coat well.
Remove, put all fruit in a large bowl.

title: bill's apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil slowly.
Stir constantly until thick.
Place in hot sterilized jars while mixture is boiling hot and seal.

title: chicken & dressing
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Tear them apart.
Retain broth.
Melt margarine in microwave.
Stir in stuffing mix.
Put half of stuffing mix in bottom of 9 x 13 dish.
Combine cream of mushroom soup with 1 can chicken broth.
Pour over stuffing mix.
Top with shredded chicken.
Mix cream of chicken soup, cream of celery soup, and 1 can chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Top with other half of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45-55 minutes.
(Cover during first 15 minutes of cooking.)

title: cheese queso dip
directions: Brown sausage.
Mix all ingredients and let simmer in crock pot until cheese is melted.

title: aunt adele's cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and sift 3 times.
Add Miracle Whip, water and vanilla.
Put into greased and cocoaed square pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Frost to your preference.

title: chocolate chip tea cakes
directions: Beat butter and powdered sugar in large bowl until creamy. Beat in vanilla, gradually beat in flour and nuts.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups morsels; roll dough into 1 inch balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in pre-heated 350° oven for 10-12 minutes or until set.
Cool completely.
Microwave remaining morsels in heavy duty plastic bag on high for 30 seconds.
Knead, microwave for additional 10-20 seconds, kneading until smooth.
Cut tiny corner from bag; squeeze to drizzle over tea cakes.
Chill until chocolate is set.

title: onion puffs
directions: Toast round of bread on one side.
Spread filling on other side.
Broil until golden.
Makes about 20 (2-inch) rounds.

title: devilish marshmallow cookies
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well with electric mixer.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cocoa; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla. (Dough will be stiff.)
Chill dough at least 30 minutes.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions until tender in small amount of water in tightly sealed saucepan.
Drain.
Mash vegetables.
Add butter or margarine, milk, salt and pepper.
Reheat to scalding.
Makes 3 to 5 servings.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix dressing, cheese and Italian seasoning.
Place chicken on greased grill over medium coals (coals will have slight glow) or rack of broiler pan 5 to 7 inches from heat.
Brush with 1/2 of the dressing mixture.
Grill or broil 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn; brush with remaining dressing mixture.
Continue grilling or broiling for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add strawberry jam and mix well; add vanilla.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Sift flour; add cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk to the creamed mixture.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon pecan cake
directions: Dust raisins and nuts with little flour.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs a little at a time.
Add alternately lemon extract, flour, nuts and raisins.
Cook at 325° for 1 1/4 hours. You can make a large cake or in loaves.
I like to make this at Christmas.

title: cucumber canapes
directions: Combine rice, tomato, parsley, onions, garlic, yogurt or sour cream, lemon juice, oil and pepper in large bowl; cover and chill.

title: hurry-up pork hash
directions: Cook onion in butter until lightly browned.
Blend in soup, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: mexicali cheese corn pudding
directions: In large bowl, whisk eggs until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together thoroughly.
Place in a
7 x 3 1/2 x 3 1/2 inch loaf pan.
Loosely cover with foil. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Drain off grease.
Top with ketchup.
Bake uncovered for 10 additional minutes.
Cool slightly before slicing.

title: chicken and broccoli braid
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Mix chopped chicken, broccoli, pepper and cheese. Add mayonnaise, garlic, dill and salt to chicken mixture. Unroll 1 package of rolls. Do not separate. Arrange longest sides of rolls across 12 x 15-inch pan. Repeat with the remaining package of rolls. Flatten rolls to make rectangle, using a rolling pin, if needed.

title: impossible turkey pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch). Sprinkle turkey, mushrooms, onions, salt and cheese in pie plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie plate. Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: fat-free pumpkin bran muffins
directions: Spray 12 muffin cups with no stick cooking spray.
In medium bowl, combine pumpkin, cereal, milk, corn syrup and egg whites. In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add pumpkin mixture, stir until well blended.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Remove. Cool on wire rack. Makes 12 muffins.
Contains 150 calories each.
No fat, 0 mg cholesterol.

title: beef ball
directions: Chop dried beef in food processor; set aside half of beef. Blend all remaining ingredients with 1/2 of beef.
Form into a ball.
Roll in remaining beef.
Serve with crackers.

title: mrs. sweeney's cheese pennies
directions: Soften cheese and margarine.
Use food processor to combine ball ingredients.
Roll dough like icebox cookies.
Cut slices very thin and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine butter, pretzels and 1/3 cup sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: peach salad
directions: Drain pineapple well; mix with peach pie filling and put in large oblong dish.
Dissolve Jell-O with boiling water; add cold water and pour over peach mixture.
Congeal.

title: russian tea
directions: Tie the cloves, cinnamon sticks, orange and lemon rinds in a bag.
Bring the 2 quarts of water to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add the bag of spices and the tea bag; steep 10 minutes.
Remove the spices and tea bag.
Add the sugar and remaining juices. Serve hot.
Makes 1/2 gallon.
Great for whatever ails you!!!

title: easy fettuccini primavera
directions: Microwave packages according to directions. Saute the Prosciutto and mushrooms in 2 teaspoons hot oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat 3 to 5 minutes or until mushrooms are tender. Add white wine, stirring to loosen particles from bottom of skillet. Add the asparagus, trimmed and cut in 2-inch pieces, and the green peas. Cook, stirring often, 3 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir in hot alfredo and Parmesan cheese. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and oleo well. Stir in coconut, nuts and raisins. Mix well and add vinegar.
Pour into pie shells and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: lobster with creamy garlic
directions: Use cooked lobster meat cut into bite size pieces.
If live Maine lobsters are used, boil lobsters 12 minutes.	Pick out meat, keeping claw meat whole and tails cut in half lengthwise.

Cover to keep warm and set aside, or prepare in advance and refrigerate. Cook pasta according to package directions while making sauce. To warm cold lobster meat, place lobster meat in colander before draining pasta.
Hot pasta/vegetable water draining through the colander will heat the lobster meat.

title: marinated grilled chicken breast
directions: Mix first six ingredients to make the marinade.
Wash the boneless skinless chicken breasts, then place in suitable covered container.
Pour in marinade, then let marinate 4 hours or better overnight.
Grill 4 to 6 minutes on each side or until done.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Cook at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in 12 x 9 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: winter berry french toast
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, melt cranberry sauce over low heat, stirring constantly.
Mix in strawberries and orange peel.
Heat just to boiling and set aside.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Grind berries and peeling of one orange. Dissolve jello, sugar and water. Let cool. Add fruit and nuts.

title: melt in your mouth treats(cookies)
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil. Place graham cracker squares on cookie sheet. Put butter, margarine and sugar in pan (after melting). Cook for 2 minutes. Pour over grahams. Sprinkle with nuts and bake at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order listed.
Refrigerate for at least an hour before serving.

title: coconut frosting
directions: In saucepan, combine milk, sugar, butter, egg and dash of salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and bubbles, about 12 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cool. Frosts top of 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake or two 8-inch layers.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together. Add soups and vegetables. Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, making a top layer of Tater Tots.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on box and drain.
In bowl, mix mayonnaise, onion, soup and eggs.
Add broccoli.
Mix in Cheez Whiz.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
After dish has browned on top, sprinkle Ritz crackers over and finish baking.
Middle should be firm.

title: haley's ham bites
directions: Remove tortillas from refrigerator.
Let stand at room temp while preparing filling.
Combine cream cheese, mayo, onions & olives.
Spread thin layer of mixture on each tortilla.
Then, place 1 or 2 pieces of ham on top.
Tightly roll up.
Wrap each one in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for 3 hours. Cut 3/4 inch diagonal slices and serve.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon and remove bone and skin.
Combine rest of ingredients and form a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans and parsley flakes.
Put a cherry on top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix the cream cheese and Ranch mix together.
Chill.
Roll into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts and chopped parsley.
Serve with crackers.
This can also be made into logs rolled in the nuts and parsley.

title: basic holiday cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture (dough should be stiff).
Refrigerate overnight in covered bowl.
Roll dough very thin, using flour on board and rolling pan.
Cut out in shapes.
Place 1 to 1 1/2-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until crisp and straw colored.
Remove cookies and cool on racks. Yields 16 dozen.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook roasts at 325° until medium rare, 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Slice roast thinly.
Slice green peppers into thin strips.
Add meat and peppers to broth.

title: omelette souffle
directions: Mix together all ingredients, saving 1 cup cheese; put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle another cup of cheese on top.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done. Turn once.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered baking dish.
Place dish in pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: apple raisin bread
directions: 1. Mix all ingredients on low. Pour into a well greased loaf pan.
2. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spudnuts
directions: Combine above ingredients; mix well.
Form into balls and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in bowl.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in corn syrup, vanilla, oats, coconut and salt.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pig eating cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour
into
3 cake pans and bake at 350° until tests done.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine in layers lettuce, tomato, onion, pepper, hamburger and cheese.
Before serving, add dressing and chips.
Mix all together.

title: favorite potato salad
directions: Cook and drain cubed potatoes.
Combine warm potatoes with onion and parsley.
Combine vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes; toss lightly with fork.
Chill for 2 hours or overnight.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix gently.
Note:
Add 3/4 teaspoon mustard to mayonnaise for extra zip.
Yields 12 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients.
Pour over 1 cup pecans in unbaked pie shell.

title: chocolate bundt cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, sour cream, oil, vanilla and rum. Beat 5 minutes; batter will be stiff. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Spoon into greased Bundt pan. Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°. Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix sugar, coconut, pecans, vanilla and graham cracker crumbs into peanut butter. Add melted butter and mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips over boiling water.
Dip balls into chocolate and place on waxed paper to dry, using fork or toothpicks.

title: greek marinated chicken with feta cheese
directions: Place chicken breasts in a saucepan with white wine and water. Simmer about 15 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove chicken; set aside to cool, then cut into 1-inch strips.
Combine oil, vinegar, capers, lemon juice, oregano, pepper and garlic to make a marinade.
Add chicken strips, cover and refrigerate at least one hour, preferably longer.

title: fresh strawberry mousse
directions: Crush the strawberries and drain the juice; reserve.
Add enough water to the juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Bring the juice to a boil and stir in gelatin; dissolve and cool.
Add the strawberries and sugar.
Whip the cream until it stands in soft peaks and fold it into the strawberry mixture.
Pour the mixture into a 2-quart ring mold or 1 1/2-quart souffle dish with 2-inch collar.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet with butter flavored Crisco.
Combine butter flavored Crisco, light brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed just until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet. Remove to kitchen counter.
Yield: about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: luscious lime cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Reserve 1/2 cup dry cake mix.
In large mixer bowl, combine remaining dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil.
Press evenly on bottom and 1 1/2 inches up sides of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In same bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add remaining eggs and reserved cake mix; beat one minute at medium speed.
Stir in lime peel, juice and vanilla.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in 3 tablespoons margarine until soft. Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients together (rice, broccoli, celery, onion, soup, milk, sour cream and cheese).

title: chili dip
directions: Brown meat and put in crock-pot.
Add the rest of the ingredients and serve warm with chips.

title: weight watcher rocky road pie
directions: For the filling, cream together the cream cheese, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Spread over crust.
Beat together the pudding, milk and water until smooth.
Spread over filling.
Top with Cool Whip, nuts and mini chips.
Must be refrigerated.

title: tomato rose
directions: Chop onions and green peppers fine.
Slice tomatoes.
Arrange in a shallow serving bowl.
Combine all remaining ingredients. Add salt.
Pour over tomatoes and chill at least 1 hour.
Serve from bowl or on lettuce leaves.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops while browning.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with above mixture and bake about one hour or until chops are tender.
Cover with foil while baking.
Bake at 350 degrees.

title: cherries in the cloud
directions: Layer the bottom
of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with slices of angel
food
cake.	Combine whipped cream, cream cheese and sugar. Spread
over
cake
layer.
Top with a layer of cherry pie filling.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream together brown sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat.
Add 3 c. flour, 1 c. milk, 1/4 tsp. salt, baking soda, cocoa and 1 1/2 tsp. vanilla and mix well.
Let batter stand for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375 degrees for 5 to 8 minutes.
When cool, place 2 halves together with filling between.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1/2 cake in punch bowl or other large bowl.
Mix large box of pudding mix and put 1/2 over cake.
Then put 1/2 of fruit, then 1/2 can pineapple and 1 carton Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Repeat procedure with the other 1/2 ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar and eggs one at a time.
Beat after each.
Add color, salt, sifted flour and cocoa.
Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Do not beat soda and vinegar. Sprinkle soda on batter and pour vinegar over it, stir well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower 6 to 8 minutes; drain well.
Place in greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Combine soup, sour cream, 1 tablespoon butter and pepper; stir well.
Pour over cauliflower.
Combine bread crumbs and 1 tablespoon butter; mix well.
Sprinkle over soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake in 3 layers.	Mix milk and lemon juice.
Pour in pineapple, then Cool Whip.	Mix and put on cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate and peanut butter pie
directions: Heat 1/2 cup peanut butter with margarine until smooth.
Stir in cracker crumbs.
Press mixture into the bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Chill.
Combine vanilla pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk and bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining peanut butter and spoon mixture into pie crust.
Chill. Combine chocolate pudding with remaining milk and bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in vanilla extract and spoon over vanilla pudding layer.
Chill.
Spread Cool Whip over pie and sprinkle with chopped peanuts, if desired.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Crush cereal in a bag with rolling pin.
Add margarine, powdered sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Form into walnut sized balls.
In top of double boiler, melt chocolate bar and chips. Add wax to chocolate mixture.
Using tongs, dip balls into melted chocolate.
Let harden on waxed paper.
Keep plenty of water in double boiler and stir chocolate as you dip balls.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: italian knots
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a bowl; set aside.
Cream the sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla until real fluffy.
Mix dry and creamed mixture together; let set in refrigerator for 10 minutes.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet by rounded tablespoonfuls.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain.
Season lightly with salt and pepper, if desired.
Shred lettuce in large bowl (Tupperware or small punch bowl).
Cut tomatoes into small chunks and cover lettuce.
Then add cheese, spreading evenly.
Top with meat.

title: shanghai shrimp
directions: Prepares in 15 minutes.
Cook green onions and ginger in oil in skillet over medium-high heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add shrimp; cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Blend cornstarch into chicken broth; stir into skillet with oranges and water chestnuts.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, until slightly thickened and heated through.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Peel sweet potatoes and cut into 3/4 inch pieces. Arrange in an ungreased 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish. In a

small saucepan, stir together sugar, cornstarch, salt and slowly stir in orange juice. Add oleo, cook stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils. Then stir 1 minute. Pour hot mixture over sweet potatoes and bake 1 hour basting occasionally.

title: grandmother's cole slaw
directions: Shred or cut cabbage in long thin strands with sharp slicing knife.
Put into a large bowl.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix well through cabbage.
Let stand while you make sauce.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Make meat mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and freeze; then thaw and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Blend catsup, juice and jelly together; pour over meatballs.
Serve hot. Makes about 60.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup and water.
Roll into 1 or 2-inch balls.
Brown.
Drain grease.
Remove meatballs from skillet.
Turn skillet on high.
Pour in the mushroom soup and water; bring to a boil, mixing the soup and water.
Return the meatballs to the skillet and simmer in the soup mixture on 200° until ready to eat.
Yields 30 to 40 meatballs.

title: mushroom croustades
directions: Cut a 2 1/2-inch circle from each bread slice; lightly spread with margarine on both sides and press into 1 3/4-inch mini muffin tin.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° until bread is lightly toasted. Cool.
(Store in airtight container overnight or freeze until ready to use, then bake for 20 minutes if filled.)

title: kugelis(a classic lithuanian dish)
directions: Peel and finely grate the potatoes and onion. Cut the bacon crosswise into thin, narrow strips. Fry until crisp. Pour fat and bacon over potato mixtures. Add hot milk. Add beaten eggs one at a time. Add salt and pepper. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 375° and bake an additional 45 minutes. Cut into squares and serve hot with sour cream or mushroom sauce.

title: best brownies
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and cocoa.
Add 2 eggs and mix well.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts, mixing well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch square, greased pan.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: leftover mashed potato soup
directions: Melt butter. Add onion and ham.
Saute until onion is tender and golden.
Add cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Stir until blended.
Add mashed potatoes and cook until hot.
May add extra milk for your own consistency.

title: my own thing cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on package.
Put rhubarb in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and gelatin.
Top with marshmallows.
Spread cake batter evenly over marshmallows. Bake at 350°
for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: chicken salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients; blend well.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce garnished with wedges of tomato, if desired.
Excellent for sandwich filling, too.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Put crumbs in bowl and cover with scalded milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in buttered casserole dish and cook for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: hearty beef and cheese pie
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, beans, garlic salt and salt; simmer while preparing crust. Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust. Combine egg and 1 cup cheese.
Spread over crust.
Spoon meat into crust.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: spinach hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix ingredients
together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: paprika potato wedges
directions: Wash potatoes and cut lengthwise into quarters.
Arrange sliced potatoes, skin down, on baking sheet and spray cut surfaces with butter-flavored Pam.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then sprinkle liberally with paprika.
Bake in 400° oven approximately 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
These go good with barbecued meats.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl beat eggs for 4 minutes on high speed; add the sugar, vanilla and butter and mix well.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking soda.
Add the flour mixture to the batter slowly and mix well.
Add the water and mix again.
Stir in the chocolate chips.
Measure 1/4 cup batter onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Be careful not to overbake.

title: sweet potato bonbons
directions: Mash sweet potatoes until light and fluffy. Add 1/4 cup butter, brown sugar, salt and orange rind; cool. Divide into 12 portions. Press each portion around a marshmallow half. Shape into a ball. Use 1/3 cup melted butter to coat the balls. Roll in crushed corn flakes, then top with a pecan. Place on lightly greased pan. Bake at 450° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Place peeled eggs in bowl or jar.
Mix vinegar, beet liquid, sugar, salt, onion and garlic.
Pour over eggs.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 days.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coffee crisps
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugars, vanilla and egg yolk. Mix well.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and coffee.
Add to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Mold 1 inch balls, place on sheet pan, flatten with bottom of cup or glass.
Bake at 375 until golden brown.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: hot clam spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with Triscuits or any other kind of crackers.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown beef and drain excess fat.
Add sauce and water and simmer 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients except lasagne noodles.
Pour 1 cup of sauce on bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Layer 3 pieces uncooked noodles over sauce.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups of sauce.
Spread half of cheese mixture over sauce.
Repeat with noodles, sauce and cheese.
Top with noodles and remaining sauce.
Cover with boil and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove foil and sprinkle with extra Parmesan cheese. Bake 10 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: baked beans
directions: Rinse beans well; add 1 teaspoon salt and cover with fresh water.
Add the onion with cloves, tomato paste and parsley; bring to boil.
Turn low and simmer covered 45 minutes.
Chop salt pork, bacon, garlic and onion very fine; set aside.
Mix molasses, mustard, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce together well.
Add bacon, garlic and onions.
Mix everything together.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on package, cooking only 9 minutes; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Set aside.
Mix together cheeses, eggs, salt, pepper, nutmeg and parsley.
Fill cooked shells with cheese mixture.
Cover bottom of baking dish with some of spaghetti sauce.
Arrange filled shells in single layer in baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over shells and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with additional cheese, if desired.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Combine chicken, onion, canned milk, olives, soup, green chilies and grated cheese in a large bowl.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pout into 1-gallon container and fill the rest of the way up with whole milk or cream.
Freeze. Makes 1 gallon.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and all ingredients, except Velveeta and spaghetti, until chicken is done.
Remove chicken, cool and debone.
Add spaghetti to broth; cook until tender.
Add Velveeta and deboned chicken.

title: salmon balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, then roll in nuts and parsley.
You can make 1 large ball or 3 small balls.
Can be wrapped securely and frozen for several weeks or more.
Makes 3 small balls.

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain pears and heat juice (1 cup) and dissolve Jell-O.
Mash pears and beat cheese together.
Add to Jell-O, Dream Whip and nuts.

title: cheese straws
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into medium size bowl.
Cut in butter with pastry cutter until mixture is crumbly.
Add cheese; toss until well blended.
Sprinkle water over mixture; mix lightly with a fork just until pastry holds together and leaves sides of bowl clean.
Roll out on a floured surface to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Cut in half lengthwise, then cut each half crosswise into 1/2-inch strips.
Lift strips one at a time; twist and place 1 inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes or until lightly golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in blender; process until smooth. Pour over last 3 ingredients.
Toss well.
Chill.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Pull chicken off bones. In 9 x 13 pan, mix soup with chicken broth. I fill pan about 3/4 way full. Add mixed vegetables and chicken. Salt and pepper.

title: chicken bites(makes 6 dozen)
directions: Clean and chop mushrooms; saute in butter 5 minutes.
Blend flour and salt; stir in cream.
Cook until thickened.
Add chives and lemon juice; set aside.
